{
    "code": "102", 
    "data": "Jawshan means “chain armour”, worn to protect the body against weapons.\nIn one of the early wars the Almighty Allah sent the text of this dua to the Holy Prophet (s.a.w.a.) from that day he discarded the armour and used to recite this dua in every battlefield.\nKafa’mee has mentioned this dua in his books “Balaadul Ameen” and “Misbah”, on the authority of Imam Ali bin Husain Al Zaynul A’abideen (a.s.) who learned it from his father, Imam Husain (a.s.), the grandson of the Holy Prophet (s.a.w.a.).\nIt is a many-sided all-purpose dua. For and on behalf of him who recites Jawshan Kabeer in the beginning of the Holy month of Ramazan, an army of seventy thousand Angels sing praises of the Almighty Allah, earning (for him) due recompense and reward.\nIf recited 3 times during the Holy month of Ramazan (particularly on “Shab-e-Qadr” nights) fire of Hell will refuse to burn the reciter and as a result the gates of paradise will be thrown open for him, because as soon as it is recited Almighty Allah takes him under his protection and keeps him safe from the onslaught of sinful temptations.\nThe Holy Prophet (s.a.w.a.) advised Imam Ali (a.s.), Bibi Faatemah (s.a.), Imam Hasan (a.s.), and Imam Husain (a.s.) to learn it by heart and recite again and again because it contains “Ism-e-A’azam” (the Great name of Allah), and make sure to tell people to write this dua on the cloth of shroud before a dead faithful person is buried as it is the best defence against all types of punishments and penalties; above all the fire of Hell will not dare to touch him.\nAt the time of war it is the most reliable defence for the faithfuls.\nRecite it before going on a journey to come back safe and successful.\nIf written text is kept in the house it is a safe insurance against fire, theft, loot and arson.\nIf written text is kept on person as Taweez it drives away misfortunes, keeps clear of accidents and brings prosperity.\nThis dua, in addition to the Holy month of Ramazan, should be recited on Fridays.\nRecite this dua once a month or at any time during a year if you are a “very busy person”, and even if that is not possible for reasons beyond your control, recite it at least once in your lifetime.\nIn all there are 100 sections in this Dua; and, in each section, 10 names or attributes of Almighty Allah are mentioned, except section 55, in which 11 attributes are recited.\nAt the end of each section recite the following:\nSUBHAANAKA YAA LAA ELAAHA ILLAA ANTAL GAUSAL GAUS KHALLISNAA MENAN NAARE YAA RAB.\nسُبْحَانَكَ يَا لَا اِلٰهَ اِلَّا اَنْتَ الْغَوْثَ الْغَوْثَ خَلِصَّنَا مِنَ النَّارِ يَا رَبْ.\nGlory be to Thee, O “there is no god save Thou”, Help! Help! Keep away the Fire from us, O Lord,\n \n(1) For Success in Difficult Works:\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA YAA ALLAAHO, YAA RAHMAAN, YAA RAHEEMO, YAA KAREEMO, YAA MOQEEMO, YAA A’ZEEMO, YAA QADEEMO, YAA A’LEEMO, YAA HALEEMO, YAA HAKEEMO.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْٓ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَآ اَللهُ یَارَحْمٰنُ یَا رَحِیْمُ یَا کَرِیْمُ یَامُقِیْمُ یَاعَظِیْمُ یَا قَدِیْمُ یَا عَلِیْمُ یَا حَلِیْمُ یَا حَکِیْمُ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O Allah, O The Beneficent, O The Merciful, O the Generous, O The Self-Subsisting, O The Great, O The Eternal, O The All-Wise, O The Indulgent, O The All-Knowing.\n(2) To Seek Help\nYAA SAYYEDAS SAADAATE, YAA MOJEEBAD DAAWAATE, YAA RAFE-A’D DARAJAATE, YAA WALIYYAL HASANAATE, YAA GHAAFERAL KHATI-A’ATE, YAA MO’TEYAL MAS-ALAATE YAA QABEELAT TAWBAATE, YAA SAAME-A’L ASWAATE, YAA A’ALEMAL KHAFIYYAATE, YAA DAAFE-A’L BALIYYAATE.\nیَاسَیِّدَ السَّادَاتِ یَا مُجِیْبَ الدَّعْوَاتِ یَارَافِعَ الدَّرَجَاتِ یَا وَلِیَّ الْحَسَنَاتِ یَا غَافِرَ الْخَطِیْئَآتِ یَا مُعْطِیَ الْمَسْئَلَاتِ یَا قَابِلَ التَّوْبَاتِ یَا سَامِعَ الْاَصْوَاتِ یَا عَالِمَ الْخَفِیَّاتِ یَا دَافِعَ الْبَلِیَّاتِ.\nO The chief of chiefs, O The Answerer of Prayers, O The Raiser of Ranks, O The Bestower of benefits, O The Forgiver of sins, O The Granter of requests, O The Acceptor of repentance, O The Hearer of voices, O The Knower of mysteries, O The Disperser of misfortunes.\n(3) To Attain Honour And Dignity\nYAA KHAYRAL GHAAFEREENA, YAA KHAYRAL FAATEHEENA, YAA KHAYRAN NAASEREENA, YAA KHAYRAL HAAKEMEENA, YAA KHAYRAR RAAZEQEENA, YAA KHAYRAL WAARESEENA, YAA KHAYRAL HAAMEDEENA, YAA KHAYRAZ ZAAKEREENA, YAA KHAYRAL MUNZELEENA, YAA KHAYRAL MOHSENEENA.\nیَاخَیْرَ الْغَافِرِیْنَ یَا خَیْرَ الْفَاتِحِیْنَ یَا خَیْرَ النَّاصِرِیْنَ یَا خَیْرَ الْحَاکِمِیْنَ یَا خَیْرَ الرَّازِقِیْنَ یَا خَیْرَ الْوَارِثِیْنَ یَا خَیْرَ الْحَامِدِیْنَ یَا خَیْرَ الذَّاکِرِیْنَ یَا خَیْرَ الْمُنْزِلِیْنَ یَا خَیْرَ الْمُحْسِنِیْنَ.\nO The Best of forgivers, O The Best of con¬querors, O The Best of helpers, O The Best of arbitrators, O The Best of nourishers, O The Best of survivors, O The Best of admirers, O The Best of rememberers, O The Best of providers, O The Best of benefactors.\n(4) To Acquire Nobility In Both The Worlds\nYAA MAN LAHUL I’ZZATO WAL JAMAALO, YAA MAN LAHUL QUDRATO WAL KAMAALO, YAA MAN LAHUL MULKO WAL JALAALO, YAA MAN HOWAL KABEERUL MOTA-A’ALO, YAA MUNSHE’AS SAHAABIS SEQAALE, YAA MAN HOWA SHADEEDUL MEHAALE, YAA MAN HOWA SAREE-U’L HESAABE, YAA MAN HOWA SHADEEDUL E’QAABE, YAA MAN I’NDAHU HUSNAS SAWAABE, YAA MAN I’NDAHU UMMUL KETAABE.\nیَا مَنْ لَہُ الْعِزَّۃُ وَ الْجَمَالُ یَا مَنْ لَہُ الْقُدْرَۃُ وَ الْکَمَالُ یَا مَنْ لَہُ الْمُلْکُ وَ الْجَلَالُ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ الْکَبِیْرُ الْمُتَعَالِ یَا مُنْشِءَ السَّحَابِ الثِّقَالِ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ شَدِیْدُ الْمِحَالِ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ سَرِیْعُ الْحِسَابِ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ شَدِیْدُ الْعِقَابِ یَا مَنْ عِنْدَہٗ حُسْنُ الثَّوَابِ یَا مَنْ عِنْدَہٗ اُمُّ الْکِتَابِ.\nO He for Whom is glory and beauty, O He for Whom is authority and perfection, O He for Whom is kingdom and majesty, O He Who is Powerful and supreme, O He Who raises the heavy clouds, O He Who is firm in strategy, O He Who is severe in punishment, O He Who is alert in reckoning, O He Who gives excellent reward, O He Who has “Ummul Kitab’ (the Mother Book).\n(5) To Achieve Renown And Success\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA YAA HANNAANO, YAA MANNAANO, YAA DAYYAANO, YAA BURHAANO, YAA SULTAANO, YAA RIZWAANO, YAA GHUFRAANO, YAA SUBHAANO, YAA MUSTA-A’ANO, YAA ZALMANNE WAL BAYAANE.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْٓ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَا حَنَّانُ یَا مَنَّانُ یَا دَیَّانُ یَا بُرْہَانُ یَا سُلْطَانُ یَا رِضْوَانُ یَا غُفْرَانُ یَا سُبْحَانُ یَا مُسْتَعَانُ یَا ذَا الْمَنِّ وَ الْبَیَانِ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O Kind, O Benevolent, O Requiter, O Clear Sign, O Sov¬ereign, O Gratifier, O Forgiver, O Praiseworthy, O He Who is called upon for help, O Master of destiny and demonstration. \n(6) To Obtain Blessings And Ranks\nYAA MAN TAWAAZA-A’ KULLO SHAY-I’N LE AZAMATEHI, YAA MANIS TASLAMA KULLO SHAY-IN LE-QUDRATEHI, YAA MAN ZALLA KULLO SHAY-IN LE-I’ZZATEHI, YAA MAN KHAZA-A’ KULLO SHAY-IN LEHAYBATEHI, YAA MANIN QADA KULLO SHAY-IN MIN KHASYATEHI, YAA MAN TASHAQQATIL JEBAALO MIN MAKHAAFATEHI, YAA MAN QAAMATIS SAMAWAATO BE-AMREHI, YAA MANIS TAQARRATIL ARZOONA BE-IZNEHI, YAA MAYN YOSABBEHUR RA’DO BE-HAMDEHI, YAA MAN LAA YA’TADI A’LAA AHLE MAMLAKATEHI.\nیَا مَنْ تَوَاضَعَ کُلُّ شَیْءٍ لِعَظَمَتِہٖ یَا مَنِ اسْتَسْلَمَ کُلُّ شَیْءٍ لِقُدْرَتِہٖ یَا مَنْ ذَلَّ کُلُّ شَیْءٍ لِعِزَّتِہٖ یَا مَنْ خَضَعَ کُلُّ شَیْءٍ لِہَیْبَتِہٖ یَا مَنِ انْقَادَ کُلُّ شَیْءٍ مِنْ خَشْیَتِہٖ یَا مَنْ تَشَقَّتِ الْجِبَالُ مِنْ مَخَافَتِہٖ یَا مَنْ قَامَتِ السَّمٰوَاتُ بِاَمْرِہٖ یَا مَنِ اسْتَقَرَّتِ الْاَرْضُوْنَ بِاِذْنِہٖ یَا مَنْ یُّسَبِّحُ الرَّعْدُ بِحَمْدِہٖ یَا مَنْ لَّا یَعْتَدِیْ عَلٰٓی اَہْلَ مَمْلَکَتِہٖ.\nO He! Everything behaves with humility be¬fore Whose greatness, O He! Everything surren¬ders to Whose power, O He! Everything submits to Whose authority, O He! Everything yields to Whose majesty, O He! Everything abides by Whose fear, O He! Mountains rend asunder by Whose awe, O He! The heavens have stood still under Whose command, O He! The earths have settled down by Whose leave, O He! The thunder sings Whose praise, O He! Who does not terrorize His subjects.\n(7) To Disperse Calamities\nYAA GHAAFERAL KHATAAYAA, YAA KAASHEFAL BALAAYAA YAA MUNTAHAR RAJAAYAA, YAA MUJZELAL A’TAAYAA, YAA WAAHEBAL HADAAYAA, YAA RAAZEQAL BARAAYAA, YAA QAAZEYAL MONAAYAA, YAA SAAMEASH SHAKAAYAA, YAA BAA-E’SAL BARAAYAA, YAA MUTLAQAL OSAARAA.\nیَا غَافِرَ الْخَطَایَا یَا کَاشِفَ الْبَلَایَا یَا مُنْتَہَی الرَّجَایَا یَا مُجْزِلَ الْعَطَایَا یَا وَاہِبَ الْہَدَایَا یَا رَازِقَ الْبَرَایَا یَا قَاضِیَ الْمَنَایَا یَا سَامِعَ الشَّکَایَا یَا بَاعِثَ الْبَرَایَا یَا مُطْلِقَ الْاُسَارٰی.\nO Pardoner of errors, O Disperser of afflictions, O Ultimate means of relief, O Awarder of rewards, O Liberal Donator of calm and peace, O Giver of daily bread to creatures, O Executor of just decrees, O Hearer of complaints, O Author of creation, O Liberator of prisoners.\n(8) To Ask Pardon\nYAA ZAL HAMDE WAS SANAA-E, YAA ZAL FAKHRE WAL BAHAA-E, YAA ZAL MAJDE WAS SANAA-E YAA ZAL AHDE WAL WAFAA-E YAA ZAL AFVE WAR RAZAA-E, YAA ZALMANNE WAL ATAA-E, YAA ZAL FAZLE WAL QAZAA-E, YAA ZAL I’ZZE WAL BAQAA-E, YAA ZAL JOODE WAS SAKHAA-E YAA ZAL AALAA-E WAN NAAMAA-E.\nیَا ذَا الْحَمْدِ وَالثَّنَآءِ یَا ذَا الْفَخْرِ وَالْبَہَآءِ یَا ذَا الْمَجْدِ وَالسَّنَآءِ یَا ذَا الْعَہْدِ وَالْوَفَآءِ یَا ذَا الْعَفْوِ وَ الرَّضَاءِ یَا ذَا الْمَنِّ وَالْعَطَآءِ یَا ذَا الْفَضْلِ وَالْقَضَآءِ یَا ذَا الْعِزِّ وَ الْبَقَآءِ یَا ذَا الْجُوْدِ وَالسَّخَآءِ یَا ذَا الْآلَآءِ وَالنَّعْمَآءِ.\nO Focus of praise and adoration, O Possessor of pride and eminence, O Master of dignity and sublimity, O Covenanter and fulfiller of promises, O Excuser and Agreer, O Benefactor, and Bestower, O Kind and (Just) Judge, O Glorious and Eternal, O Munificent and Bounteous, O High and Benign.\n(9) To Clear Away Fear And Disease\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA,YAA MAANE-O’, YAA DAAFE-O’, YAA RAAFE-O YAA SAANE-O YAA NAAFE-O’, YAA SAAME-O’, YAA JAAME-O YAA SHAAFE-O YAA WAASE-O’, YAA MOOSE-O’.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْٓ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَا مَانِعُ یَا دَافِعُ یَارَافِعُ یَا صَانِعُ یَا نَافِعُ یَا سَامِعُ یَا جَامِعُ یَا شَافِعُ یَاوَاسِعُ یَامُوْسِعُ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O Preventer, O Disperser, O Raiser, O Maker, O Benefactor, O Listener, O Gatherer, O Rescuer, O Enricher, O Increaser.\n(10) To Get Approval Of Conduct\nYAA SAANE-A KULLE MASNOO-I’N, YAA KHAALEQA KULLE MAKHLOOQIN, YAA RAAZEQA KULLE MARZOOQIN, YAA MAALEKA KULLE MAMLOOKIN. YA KAASHEFA KULLE MAKROOBIN, YAA FAAREJA KULLE MAHMOOMIN, YAA RAAHEMA KULLE MARHOOMIN, YAA NAASERA KULLE MAKHZOOLIN, YAA SAATERA KULLE MA’YOOBIN, YAA MALJA-A KULLE MATROODIN.\nیَا صَانِعَ کُلِّ مَصْنُوْعٍ یَا خَالِقَ کُلِّ مَخْلُوْقٍ یَا رَازِقَ کُلِّ مَرْزُوْقٍ یَا مَالِکَ کُلِّ مَمْلُوْکٍ یَا کَاشِفَ کُلِّ مَکْرُوْبٍ یَا فَارِجَ کُلِّ مَہْمُوْمٍ یَا رَاحِمَ کُلِّ مَرْحُوْمٍ یَا نَاصِرَ کُلِّ مَخْذُوْلٍ یَا سَاتِرَ کُلِّ مَعْیُوْبٍ یَا مَلْجَاَ کُلِّ مَطْرُوْدٍ.\nO maker of all that has been made, O Creator of all that has been created, O Provider of daily bread to all who are in need of food, O Master of all servants (whole creation), O Expeller of all hardships, O Reliever of all grief and sorrow, O Merciful to all those who seek mercy, O Helper of all those who have been forsaken, O Concealer of all defects, O Refuge of all those who have been thrown out.\n(11) To Avoid Evil And Gain Prosperity\nYAA UDDATI I’NDA SHIDDATI, YAA RAJAA-E’E I’NDA MOSEEBATI, YAA MOONESI I’NDA WAH-SHATEE, YAA SAAHEBEE I’NDA GHOORBATI, YAA WALIYYEE I’NDA NE’MATEE, YAA GHEYAASEE I’NDA KOORBATEE, YAA DALEELEE I’NDA HAYRATEE, YAA GHENAA-E’E I’NDAF TEQAARI YAA MALJA-E’E I’NDAZ TERAAREE, YAA MO-E’ENEE I’NDA MAFZA-E’E.\nیَا عُدَّتِیْ عِنْدَ شِدَّتِیْ یَا رَجَآئِیْ عِنْدَ مُصِیْبَتِیْ یَا مُوْنِسِیْ عِنْدَ وَحْشَتِیْ یَا صَاحِبِیْ عِنْدَ غُرْبَتِیْ یَا وَلِیِّیْ عِنْدَ نِعْمَتِیْ یَا غِیَاثِیْ عِنْدَ کُرْبَتِیْ یَا دَلِیْلِیْ عِنْدَ حَیْرَتِیْ یَا غَنَآئِیْ عِنْدَ افْتِقَارِیْ یَا مَلْجَائِیْ عِنْدَ اضْطِرَارِیْ یَا مُعِیْنِیْ عِنْدَ مَفْزَعِیْ.\nO My Support in my hardship, O my Hope in my misfortune, O my Sympathizer in my loneli¬ness, O my Companion in my journey, O my Ally in my happiness, O my Supporter in my distress, O my Guide in my confusion, O my Advantage in my bliss, O my Sanctuary in my misery, O my Succourer in my despair.\n(12) To Dismiss Affliction and Secure Good Fortune\nYAA A’LLAAMAL GHOYOOBE, YAA GHAFFAARAZ ZONOOBE YAA SATTAARAL O’YOOBE, YAA KAASHEFAL KOROOBE, YAA MOQALLEBAL QOLOOBE, YAA TABEEBAL QOLOOBE YAA MONAWWERAL QOLOOBE YAA ANEESAL QOLOOBE, YAA MOFARREJAL HOMOOME, YAA MONAFFESAL GHOMOOME.\nیَا عَلاَّمَ الْغُیُوْبِ یَا غَفَّارَ الذُّنُوْبِ یَا سَتَّارَ الْعُیُوْبِ یَا کَاشِفَ الْکُرُوْبِ یَا مُقَلِّبَ الْقُلُوْبِ یَا مُنَوِّرَ الْقُلُوْبِ یَا طَبِیْبَ الْقُلُوْبِ یَا اَنِیْسَ الْقُلُوْبِ یَا مُفَرِّجَ الْہُمُوْمِ یَا مُنَفِّسَ الْغُمُوْمِ.\nO Perceiver of the invisible, O Coverer of fault, O Concealer of shortcomings, O Reliever of pains, O Converter of hearts, O Healer of hearts, O Enlightner of hearts, O Consoler of hearts, O Dispeller of worries, O Disperser of grieves.\n(13) To Cure Eye Disease\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA, YAA JALEELO, YAA JAMEELO, YAA WAKEELO, YAA KAFEELO, YAA DALEELO, YAA QABEELO, YAA MODEELO, YAA MONEELO, YAA MOQEELO YAA MOHEELO.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَا جَلِیْلُ یَا جَمِیْلُ یَا وَکَیْلُ یَا کَفِیْلُ یَا دَلِیْلُ یَا قَبِیْلُ یَا مُدِیْلُ یَا مُنِیْلُ یَا مُقِیْلُ یَا مُحِیْلُ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy Name, O Magnificent, O Elegant, O Protector, O Satisfier, O Demonstrator, O Guarantor, O Enricher, O Favourer, O Acquitter, O Vivifier.\n(14) To Increase Wealth\nYAA DALEELAL MOTAHAYYAREENA, YAA GHEYAASAL MUSTAGHEESEENA, YAA SAREEKHAL MUSTASREKHEENA, YAA JAARAL MUSTAJEEREENA, YAA AMAANAL KHAA-E-FEENA, YAA AWNAL MO’MENEENA, YAA RAAHEMAL MASAAKEENA, YAA MAL-JA-A’L A’ASEENA, YAA GHAAFERAL MUZNEBEENA, YAA MOJEEBA DA’WATIL MUZTARREENA.\nیَا دَلِیْلَ الْمُتَحَیِّرِیْنَ یَا غِیَاثَ الْمُسْتَغِیْثِیْنَ یَا صَرِیْخَ الْمُسْتَصْرِخِیْنَ یَا جَارَ الْمُسْتَجِیْرِیْنَ یَآ اَمَانَ الْخَآئِفِیْنَ یَا عَوْنَ الْمُؤْمِنِیْنَ یَا رَاحِمَ الْمَسَاکِیْنَ یَا مَلْجَاَ الْعَاصِیْنَ یَا غَافِرَ الْمُذْنِبِیْنَ یَا مُجِیْبَ دَعْوَۃِ الْمُضْطَرِّیْنَ.\nO Guide of the bewildered, O Helper of the help-seekers, O Answerer to the out criers, O Pro¬tector of the protection-seekers, O Asylum for the afraid, O Escort of the faithful, O Provider of the poor, O Hope of the disobedient, O Pardoner of the sinners, O Comforter of the restless.\n(15) To Ask For More Benefits\nYAA ZAL JOODE WAL EHSAANE, YAA ZAL FAZLE WAL IMTENAANE, YAA ZAL AMNE WAL AMAANE, YAA ZAL QUDSE WAS SUBHAANE, YAA ZAL HIKMATE WAL BAYAANE, YAA ZAR-RAHMATE WAR RIZWAANE, YAA ZAL HUJJATE WAL BURHAANE, YAA ZAL A’ZMATE WAS SULTAANE, YAA ZAR RAAFATE WAL MUSTA-A’ANE, YAA ZAL A’FVE WAL GHUFRAANE.\nیَا ذَا الْجُوْدِ وَالْاِحْسَانِ یَا ذَا الْفَضْلِ وَالْاِمْتِنَانِ یَا ذَا الْاَمْنِ وَالْاَمَانِ یَا ذَا الْقُدْسِ وَالسُّبْحَانِ یَا ذَا الْحِکْمَۃِ وَالْبَیَانِ یَا ذَا الرَّحْمَۃِ وَالرِّضْوَانِ یَا ذَا الْحُجَّۃِ وَالْبُرْہَانِ یَا ذَا الْعَظَمَۃِ وَالسُّلْطَانِ یَا ذَا الرَّافَۃِ وَالْمُسْتَعَانِ یَا ذَا الْعَفْوِ وَالْغُفْرَانِ.\nO Lord of abundance and benefits, O Lord of superabundance and favours, O Lord of peace and security, O Lord of purity and glory, O Lord of wisdom and evidence, O Lord of mercy and ap¬proval, O Lord of argument and proof, O Lord of grandeur and sovereignty, O Lord of sublimity and support, O Lord of amnesty and forgiveness.\n(16) To Solve Problems\nYAA MAN HOWA RABBO KULLE SHAY-IN, YAA MAN HOWA ELAAHO KULLE SHAY-IN, YAA MAN HOWA KHAALEQO KULLE SHAY-IN, YAA MAN HOWA SAALEHO KULLE SHAY-IN, YAA MAN HOWA QABLA KULLE SHAY-IN, YAA MAN HOWA BA’DA KULLE SHAY-IN, YAA MAN HOWA FAWQA KULLE SHAY-IN, YAA MAN HOWA A’ALEMUN BEKULLE SHAY-IN, YAA MAN HOWA QAADERUN A’LAA KULLE SHAY-IN, YAA MAN HOWA YABQAA WA YAFNAA KULLE SHAY-IN.\nیَا مَنْ ہُوَ رَبُّ کُلِّ شَیْءٍ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ اِلٰہُ کُلِّ شَیْءٍ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ خَالِقُ کُلِّ شَیْءٍ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ صَانِعُ کُلِّ شَیْءٍ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ قَبْلَ کُلِّ شَیْءٍ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ بَعْدَ کُلِّ شَیْءٍ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فَوْقَ کُلِّ شَیْءٍ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ عَالِمٌ بِکُلِّ شَیْءٍ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ قَادِرٌ عَلٰی کُلِّ شَیْءٍ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ یَبْقٰی وَ یَفْنٰی کُلُّ شَیْءٍ.\nO He Who is the provider of means of liveli¬hood to everything, O He Who is God of every¬thing, O He Who is the Creator of everything, O He Who is the Fashioner of everything, O He Who is prior to everything, O He Who is beyond every¬thing, O He Who is over and above everything, O He Who is Knower of everything, O He Who is Dominant over everything, O He Who is Ever-Living while everything dies.\n(17) To Accomplish Difficult Undertakings\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA, YAA MO’MENO YAA MOHAYMENO, YAA MOKAWWENO YAA MOLAQQENO, YAA MOBAYYENO YAA MOHAWWENO YAA MOMAKKENO, YAA MOZAYYENO, YAA MO’LENO, YAA MOQASSEMO.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَا مُؤْمِنُ یَا مُہَیْمِنُ یَا مُکَوِّنُ یَا مُلَقِّنُ یَا مُبَیِّنُ یَا مُہَوِّنُ یَا مُمَکِّنُ یَا مُزَیِّنُ یَا مُعْلِنُ یَا مُقَسِّمُ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name O Gen¬uine, O Guardian, O Self-Existing, O Addresser (to the dead), O Revealer, O Gentle, O Accomplisher, O Beautifier, O Proclaimer, O Distributor.\n(18) To Increase Livelihood\nYAA MAN HOWA FEE MULKEHI MOQEEMUN, YAA MAN HOWA FEE SULTAANEHI QADEEMUN, YAA MAN HOWA FEE JALAALEHI A’ZEEMUN, YAA MAN HOWA A’LAA E’BAADEHI RAHEEMUN, YAA MAN HOWA BE-KULLE SHAY-IN A’LEEMUN, YAA MAN HOWA BE-MAN A’SAAHO HALEEMUN, YAA MAN HOWA BE-MAN RAJAAHO KAREEMUN, YAA MAN HOWA FEE SUN-EHI HAKEEMUN, YAA MAN HOWA FEE HIKMATEHI LATEEFUN, YAA MAN HOWA FEE LUTFEHI QADEEMUN.\nیَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ مُلْکِہٖ مُقِیْمٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ سُلْطَانِہٖ قَدِیْمٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ جَلاَلِہٖ عَظِیْمٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ عَلٰی عِبَادِہٖ رَحِیْمٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ بِکُلِّ شَیْءٍ عَلِیْمٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ بِمَنْ عَصَاہُ حَلِیْمٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ بِمَنْ رَجَاہُ کَرِیْمٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ صُنْعِہٖ حَکِیْمٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ حِکْمَتِہٖ لَطِیْفٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ لُطْفِہٖ قَدِیْمٌ.\nO He Who is Ever-Abiding in His (boundless) kingdom, O He Who is forever powerful in His absolute power, O He Who is Great in His majesty, O He Who is Merciful to His servants, O He Who is fully aware of all things, O He Who is Forbear¬ing towards the disobedient, O He Who is Gener-ous to the requester, O He Who is Wise in His act of creating, O He Who is Subtle in His wisdom, O He Who is ever more Benign in his benevolence.\n(19) To Attain Distinction\nYAA MAN LAA YURJAA ILLA FAZLAHU, YAA MAN LAA YUS-A’LO ILLAA A’FWOHU, YAA MAN LAA YUNZARO ILLAA BIRROHU, YAA MAN LA YOKHAAFO ILLAA A’DLOHU, YAA MAN LA YADOOMO ILLAA MULKAHU, YAA MAN LAA SULTAANA ILLA SULTAANOHU, YAA MAN WASE-A’T KULLA SHAY-IN RAHMATOHU, YAA MAN SABAQAT RAHMATOHU GHAZABAHU, YAA MAN AHAATA BE-KULLE SHAY-IN I’LMOHU, YAA MAN LAYSA AHADUNN MISLOHU.\nیَا مَنْ لَا یُرْجٰی اِلَّا فَضْلُہٗ یَا مَنْ لَا یُسْئَلُ اِلَّا عَفْوُہٗ یَا مَنْ لَا یُنْظَرُ اِلَّا بِرُّہٗ یَا مَنْ لَا یُخَافُ اِلَّا عَدْلُہٗ یَا مَنْ لَا یَدُوْمُ اِلَّا مُلْکُہٗ یَا مَنْ لَا سُلْطَانَ اِلَّا سُلْطَانُہٗ یَا مَنْ وَسِعَتْ کُلَّ شَیْءٍ رَحْمَتُہٗ یَا مَنْ سَبَقَتْ رَحْمَتُہٗ غَضَبَہٗ یَا مَنْ اَحَاطَ بِکُلِّ شَیْءٍ عِلْمُہٗ یَا مَنْ لَیْسَ اَحَدٌ مِثْلَہٗ.\nO He from whom nothing but favor is expect¬ed, O He from Whom nothing but pardon is obtained, O He from Who nothing but good comes out, O He Who is not feared but for His justice, O He Whose Kingdom alone (and nothing) is eternal, O He Whose Sovereignty alone (and nothing) is prevailing, O He Whose Mercy encompasses ev¬erything, O He Whose compassion gets the better of His wrath, O He Whose wisdom comprehends everything, O He Who has no equal.\n(20) To Disperse Worries \nYAA FAAREJAL HAMME, YAA KAASHEFAL GHAMME, YAA GHAAFERAZ ZAMBE, YAA QAABELAT TAWBE, YAA KHAALEQAL KHALQE, YAA SAADEQAL WA’DE YAA MOOFEYAL A’HDE YAA A’ALEMAS SIRRE, YAA FAALEQAL HABBE, YAA RAAZEQAL ANAAME.\nیَا فَارِجَ الْہَمِّ یَا کَاشِفَ الْغَمِّ یَا غَافِرَ الذَّنْبِ یَا قَابِلَ التَّوْبِ یَا خَالِقَ الْخَلْقِ یَا صَادِقَ الْوَعْدِ یَا مُوْفِیَ الْعَہْدِ یَا عَالِمَ السِّرِّ یَا فَالِقَ الْحَبِّ یَا رَازِقَ الْاَنَامِ.\nO Disperser of worry, O Mitigator of sorrow, O Forgiver of Sins, O Acceptor of repentance, O Creator of creation, O Sincere Fulfiller of promis¬es, O Accomplisher of covenants, O Knower of secrets, O Splitter of seed, O Sustainer of mankind.\n(21) To Plead For Forgiveness Of Sins\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA YAA A’LIYYO, YAA WAFIYYO, YAA GHANIYYO, YAA MALIYYO, YAA KHAFIYYO, YAA RAZIYYO, YAA ZAKIYYO, YAA BADIYYO, YAA QAWIYYO, YAA WALIYYO.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَا عَلِیُّ یَا وَفِیُّ یَا غِنِیُّ یَا مَلِیُّ یَا حَفِیُّ یَا رِضِیُّ یَا زَکِیُّ یَا بَدِیُّ یَا قَوِیُّ یَا وَلِیُّ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O High, O Perfect, O Independent, O Rich, O Hidden, O Assenter, O Intelligent, O First, O Mighty, O Guardian.\n(22) To Increase Livelihood\nYAA MAN AZHARAL JAMEEL WA YAA MAN SATARAL QABEEHA WA YAA MAN LAM YO-AAKHIZ BIL JARIRATE WA YAA MAN LAM YAHTEKIS SITRA, YAA A’ZEEMAL A’FVE YAA HASANAT TAJAAWOZE, YAA WAASE-A’L MAGHFERATE, YAA BAASETAL YADAYNE BIRRAHMATE, YAA SAAHEBA KULLE NAJWAA, YAA MUNTAHAA KULLE SHAKWAA.\nیَا مَنْ اَظْہَرَ الْجَمِیْلَ وَ يَا مَنْ سَتَرَ الْقَبِیْحَ وَ یَا مَنْ لَّمْ یُؤَاخِذُ بِالْجَرِیْرَۃِ وَ یَا مَنْ لَّمْ یَہْتِکِ السِّتْرَ یَا عَظِیْمَ الْعَفْوِ یَا حَسَنَ التَّجَاوُزِ یَا وَاسِعَ الْمَغْفِرَۃِ یَا بَاسِطَ الْیَدَیْنِ بِالرَّحْمَۃِ یَا صَاحِبَ کُلِّ نَجْوٰی یَا مُنْتَہٰی کُلِّ شَکْوٰی.\nO He Who exposes beauty, O He Who con¬ceals ugliness, O He Who does not call to account for transgressions, O He Who does not withdraw protection, O. The Great Forgiver, O Dispensator of fair treatment, O Boundless forgiver, O Spread¬er of unlimited mercy, O Sharer of mutual secrets, O Last Resort of all complaints.\n(23) To Get More Beneficence\nYAA ZAN NE-A’MATIS SAABEGHATE, YAA ZARRAHMATIL WAASE-A’TE, YAA ZALMINNATIS SAABEQATE, YAA ZAL HIKMATIL BAALEGHATE, YAA ZAL QUDRATIL KAAMELATE, YAA ZAL HUJJATIL QAATE-A’TE, YAA ZAL KARAAMATIZ ZAAHERATE, YAA ZAL I’ZZATID DAA-EMATE, YAA ZAL QUWWATIL MATEENATE, YAA ZAL A’ZAMATIL MANEE-A’TE.\nیَا ذَا النِّعْمَۃِ السَّابِغَۃِ یَا ذَالرَّحْمَۃِ الْوَاسِعَۃِ یَا ذَا الْمِنَّۃِ السَّابِقَۃِ یَا ذَا الْحِکْمَۃِ الْبَالِغَۃِ یَا ذَا الْقُدْرَۃِ الْکَامِلَۃِ یَا ذَا الْحُجَّۃِ الْقَاطِعَۃِ یَا ذَا الْکَرَامَۃِ الظَّاہِرَۃِ یَا ذَا الْعِزَّۃِ الدَّآئِمَۃِ یَا ذَا الْقُوَّۃِ الْمَتِیْنَۃِ یَا ذَا الْعَظَمَۃِ الْمَنِیْعَۃِ.\nO Master of abundant bounties, O Master of plenteous mercy, O Master of incomparable kind¬ness, O Master of penetrating wisdom, O Master of absolute power, O Master of conclusive argument, O Master of evident generosity, O Master of everlasting dignity, O Master of strong might, O Master of impregnable greatness.\n(24) To Receive Allah’s Bliss\nYAA BADEEA’S SAMAAWAATE, YAA JAA-E’LAZ ZOLOMAATE, YAA RAAHEMAL ABARAATE, YAA MOQEELAL ASARAATE, YAA SAATERAL AWRAATE, YAA MOH-YEYAL AMWAATE, YAA MUNZELAL-AAYAATE, YAA MOZA’-E’FAL HASANAATE, YAA MAAHEYAS SAYYE-AATE, YAA SHADEEDAN NAQEMAATE.\nیَا بَدِیْعَ السَّمٰوٰتِ یَا جَاعِلَ الظُّلُمَاتِ یَا رَاحِمَ الْعَبَرَاتِ یَا مُقِیْلَ الْعَثَرَاتِ یَا سَاتِرَ الْعَوْرَاتِ یَا مُحْیِیَ الْاَمْوَاتِ یَا مُنْزِلَ الْاٰیاَتِ یَا مُضَعِّفَ الْحَسَنَاتِ یَا مَاحِیَ السَّیِّئَاتِ یَا شَدِیْدَ النَّقَمَاتِ.\nO Creator of heavens, O Activator of Dark¬ness, O Pitier of tears, O Ignorer of errors, O Concealer of ignominy, O Revivifier of the dead, O Revealer of signs, O Multiplier of virtues, O Obliterator of vices, O Severe Reckoner,\n(25) To Dispel Ill Luck And Seek Fortune\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA, YAA MOSAWWERO, YAA MOQADDERO, YAA MODABBERO, YAA MOTAH-HERO, YAA MONAWWERO YAA MOYASSERO, YAA MOBASH-SHERO, YAA MONAZ-ZERO, YAA MOQAD-DEMO, YAA MO-A’KH-KHERO.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَا مُصَوِّرُ یَا مُقَدِّرُ یَا مُدَبِّرُ یَامُطَہِّرُ یَا مُنَوِّرُ یَا مُیَسِّرُ یَا مُبَشِّرُ یَا مُنْذِرُ یَا مُقَدِّمُ یَا مُؤَخِّرُ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O Fashioner, O Pre-Ordainer, O Statesman, O Puri¬fier, O Illuminator, O Sufficer, O Communicator of glad tidings, O Warner, O Foremost, O Postponer.\n(26) To Get Rid Of Fever\nYAA RABBAL BAYTIL HARAAME, YAA RABBASH SHAHRIL HARAAME, YAA RABBAL BALAADIL HARAAME,YAA RABBAR-RUKNE WAL MAQAAME, YAA RABBAL MASH-A’RIL HARAAME, YAA RABBAL MASJEDIL HARAAME, YAA RABBAL HILLE WAL HARAAME, YAA RABBAN NOORE WAZ ZALAAME, YAA RABBAT TAHIYYATE WAS SALAAME, YAA RABBAL QOODRATE FIL ANAAME.\nیَا رَبَّ الْبَیْتِ الْحَرَامِ یَا رَبَّ الشَّہْرِ الْحَرَامِ یَا رَبَّ الْبَلَدِ الْحَرَامِ یَا رَبَّ الرُّکْنِ وَالْمَقَامِ یَا رَبَّ الْمَشْعَرِ الْحَرَامِ يَا رَبَّ الْمَسْجِدِ الْحَرَامِ یَا رَبَّ الْحِلِّ وَالْحَرَامِ یَا رَبَّ النُّوْرِ وَالظَّلاَمِ یَا رَبَّ التَّحِیَّۃِ وَ السَّلاَمِ یَا رَبَّ الْقُدْرَۃِ فِی الْاَنَامِ.\nO Lord of the Holy House, O Lord of the Holy month, O Lord of the Holy city, O Lord of Rukn (Trust) and Maqaam (Dignity), O Lord of Mashril Haraam, (Place where Hajis pray and offer sacri¬fice), O Lord of the Holy Mosque, O Lord (Ordainer) of Hill (Lawful) and Haraam (Unlawful), O Lord of light and darkness, O Lord of life (Keeping alive) and peace, O Lord of might over created beings.\n(27) To Dismiss Fear Of Rulers (Recite 20 times)\nYAA AHKAMAL HAAKEMEENA YAA A-A’DALAL A’ADELEENA, YAA ASDAQAS SAADEQEENA, YAA ATHARAT TAAHEREENA, YAA AHSANAL KHAALEQEENA, YAA ASRA-A’L HAASEBEENA, YAA ASMA-A’S SAAME-E’ENA, YAA ABSARAN NAAZEREENA, YAA ASHFA-A’SH SHAAFE-E’ENA, YAA AKRAMAL AKRAMEENA.\nیَآ اَحْکَمَ الْحَاکِمِیْنَ یَآ اَعْدَلَ الْعَادِلِیْنَ یَآ اَصْدَقَ الصَّادِقِیْنَ یَآ اَطْہَرَ الطَّاہِرِیْنَ یَآ اَحْسَنَ الْخَالِقِیْنَ یَآ اَسْرَعَ الْحَاسِبِیْنَ یَا اَسْمَعَ السَّامِعِیْنَ یَآ اَبْصَرَ النَّاظِرِیْنَ یَآ اَشْفَعَ الشَّافِعِیْنَ یَآ اَکْرَمَ الْاَکْرَمِیْنَ.\nO The Wisest of all rulers, O The Most equi¬table of all judges, O The Truest of the true, O The Purest of the pure, O The Best of all creators, O The Quickest of all reckoner, O The Best of all hearers, O The Best of all observers, O The Best of all intercessors, O The Most Noble of all nobles.\n(28) To Cure Migraine\nYAA E’MAADA MAN LAA E’MAADA LAHU, YAA SANADA MAN LAA SANADA LAHU, YAA ZUKHRA MAN LAA ZUKHRA LAHU, YAA HIRZA MAN LA HIRZA LAHU, YAA GHEYAASA MAN LAA GHEYAASA LAHU, YAA FAKHRA MAN LAA FAKHRA LAHU, YAA I’ZZA MAN LA I’ZZA LAHU, YAA MO-E’ENA MAN LAA MO-E’ENA LAHU, YAA ANEESA MAN LAA ANEESA LAHU, YAA AMAANA MAN LAA AMANA LAHU.\nیَاعِمَادَ مَنْ لَا عِمَادَ لَہٗ یَا سَنَدَ مَنْ لَا سَنَدَ لَہٗ یَا ذُخْرَ مَنْ لَا ذُخْرَلَہٗ یَا حِرزَ مَنْ لَا حِرْزَلَہٗ یَا غِیَاثَ مَنْ لَا غِیَاثَ لَہٗ یَا فَخْرَ مَنْ لَا فَخْرَ لَہٗ یَا عِزَّ مَنْ لَا عِزَّ لَہٗ یَا مُعِیْنَ مَنْ لَا مُعِیْنَ لَہٗ یَآ اَنِیْسَ مَنْ لَا اَنِیْسَ لَہٗ یَآ اَمَانَ مَنْ لَا اَمَانَ لَہٗ.\nO Support of him who has no support, O Surety of him who has nothing to lean upon, O Repository of him who has no provision, O Protection of him who has no protection, O Succourer of him who has been forsaken, O Pride of him who has nothing to be proud of, O Glory of him who has no distinction, O Help of him who is helpless, O Companion of him who has no com¬rade, O Refuge of him who has no shelter. \n(29) To Build Up Defense\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA YAA A’ASEMO, QAA-EMO, YAA DAA-E’MO, YAA RAAHEMO, YAA SAALEMO YAA HAKEMO, A’ALEMO, YAA QAASEMO, YAA QAABEZO, YAA BAASETO.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَا عَاصِمُ یَا قَآئِمُ یَا دَآئِمُ یَا رَاحِمُ یَا سَالِمُ یَاحَاکِمُ یَا عَالِمُ یَا قَاسِمُ یَا قَابِضُ یَا بَاسِطُ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O Defender, O Ever-Lasting, O Ever-Living, O Mer¬ciful, O Dependable, O Ruler, O Knower, O Dis¬tributor, O Seizer, O Expansive.\n(30) To Win War\nYAA A’ASEMA MANIS TA’SAMAHU, YAA RAAHEMA MANIS TARHAMAHU, YAA GHAAFERA MANIS TAGHFERAHU, YAA NAASERA MANIS TANSARAHU, YAA HAAFEZA MANIS TAHFAZAHU YAA MUKREMA MANIS TAKRAMAHU, YAA MURSHEDA MANIS TARSHADAHU, YAA SAREEKHA MANIS TASRAKHAHU, YAA MO-E’ENA MANIS TA-A’ANAHU, YAA MOGHEESA MANIS TAGHASAHU.\nیَا عَاصِمَ مَنِ اسْتَعْصَمَہٗ یَا رَاحِمَ مَنِ اسْتَرْحَمَہٗ یَا غَافِرَ مَنِ اسْتَغْفَرَہُ یَا نَاصِرَ مَنِ اسْتَنْصَرَہٗ یَا حَافِظَ مَنِ اسْتَحْفَظَہٗ یَا مُکْرِمَ مَنِ اسْتَکْرَمَہٗ یَا مُرْشِدَ مَنِ اسْتَرْشَدَہٗ یَا صَرِیْخَ مَنِ اسْتَصْرَخَہٗ یَا مُعِیْنَ مَنِ اسْتَعَانَہٗ یَا مُغِیْثَ مَنِ اسْتَغَاثَہٗ.\nO Defender of him who seeks His aid, O Pitier of him who seeks His mercy, O Pardoner of him who seeks His pardon, O Rescuer of him who seeks His aid, O Protector of him who seeks His protection, O Favourer of him who seeks His favour, O Leader of him who seeks His guidance, O Succourer of him who seeks His succour, O Helper of him who seeks His help, O Supporter of him who seeks His support.\n(31) To Cure Eye Disease\nYAA A’ZEEZAN LAA YOZAAMO, YAA LATEEFAL LAA YORAAMO, YAA QAYYOOMAL LAA YANAAMO, YAA DAA-EMAL LAA YAFOOTO, YAA HAYYAN LAA YAMOOTO, YAA MALEKAL LAA YAZOOLO, YAA BAAQEYAL LAA YAFNA YAA A’ALEMAL LAA YAJHALO, YAA SAMADAL LAA YUT-A’MO, YAA QAWIYYAL LAA YUZ-A’FO.\nیَا عَزِیْزًا لَّا یُضَامُ یَا لَطِیْفًا لَّا یُرَامُ یَا قَیُّوْمًا لَّا یَنَامُ یَا دَآئِمًا لَّا یَفُوْتُ یَا حَیًّا لَّا یَمُوْتُ یَا مَلِکًا لَّا یَزُوْلُ یَا بَاقِیًا لَّا یَفْنٰی یَا عَالِمًا لَّا یَجْہَلُ یَا صَمَدًا لَّا یُطْعَمُ یَآ قَوِیًّا لَّا یَضْعُفُ.\nO Great Who is never humbled, O Subtle Who is unperceivable, O Durable Who slumbers not, O Ever-Lasting Who is indestructible, O Ever-Liv¬ing Who is not mortal, O Master Who never loses control, O Eternal Who is never non-existent, O Knower Who is never ignorant, O Endurer Who needs no sustenance, O Mighty Who is never undermined.\n(32) To Subdue Enemies\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA, YAA AHADO, YAA WAAHEDO, YAA SHAAHEDO , YAA MAAJEDO, YAA HAAMEDO YAA RAASHEDO, YAA BAA-ESO, YAA WAARESO, YAA ZAARRO, YAA NAAFE-O’.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَآ اَحَدُ یَا وَاحِدُ یَا شَاہِدُ یَا مَاجِدُ یَا حَامِدُ یَا رَاشِدُ یَا بَاعِثُ یَا وَارِثُ یَا ضَآرُّ یَا نَافِعُ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O Single, O One, O Witness, O Praised, O Glorious, O Guide, O Author, O Possessor, O Punisher, O Benefactor.\n(33) To Have Courage To Face Rulers\nYAA A-A’ZAMA MIN KULLE A’ZEEMIN, YAA AKRAMA MIN KULLE KAREEMIN, YAA ARHAMA MIN KULLE RAHEEMIN, YAA A-A’LAMA MIN KULLE A’LEEMIN YAA AHKAMA MIN KULLE HAKEEMIN, YAA AQDAMA MIN KULLE QADEEMIN, YAA AKBARA MIN KULLE KABEERIN, YAA ALTAFA MIN KULLE LATEEFIN, YAA AJALLA MIN KULLE JALEELIN, YAA A-A’ZZA MIN KULLE A’ZEEZIN.\nيَا اَعْظَمَ مِنْ كُلِّ عَظِيْمٍ يَا اَكْرَمَ مِنْ كُلِّ كَرِيْمٍ يَا اَرْحَمَ مِنْ كُلِّ رَحِيْمٍ يَا اَعْلَمَ مِنْ كُلِّ عَلِيْمٍ يَا اَحْكَمَ مِنْ كُلِّ حَكِيْمٍ يَا اَقْدَمَ مِنْ كُلِّ قَدِيْمٍ يَا اَكْبَرَ مِنْ كُلِّ كَبِيْرٍ يَا اَلْطَفَ مِنْ كُلِّ لَطِيْفٍ يَا اَجَلَّ مِنْ كُلِّ جَلِيْلٍ يَا اَعَزَّ مِنْ كُلِّ عَزِيْزٍ.\nO The Supreme among (all) the chiefs, O The Most Generous among (all) the generous, O The Most Merciful among (all) the Merciful, O the Most Learned among (all) the learned, O The Wisest among (all) the wise, O The Foremost among (all) the formers, O The Greatest among (all) the greats, O The Most Subtle among (all) the refined, O The Most Sublime among (all) the magnificent, O The Mightiest among (all) the mighty.\n(34) To Seek Safeguard Against Jinn\nYAA KAREEMAS SAFHE, YAA A’ZEEMAL MANNE, YAA KASEERAL KHAYRE, YAA QADEEMAL FAZLE, YAA DAA-E’MAL LUTFE, YAA LATIFAS SUN-E’, YAA MONAFFESAL KARBE, YAA KASHEFAZ ZURRE, YAA MAALEKAL MULKE, YAA KAAZEYAL HAQQE.\nیَا کَرِیْمَ الصَّفْحِ یَا عَظِیْمَ الْمَنِّ یَا کَثِیْرَ الْخَیْرِ یَا قَدِیْمَ الْفَضْلِ یَا دَآئِمَ اللُّطْفِ یَا لَطِیْفَ الصُّنْعِ یَا مُنَفِّسَ الْکَرْبِ یَا کَاشِفَ الضُّرِّ یَا مَالِکَ الْمُلْکِ یَا قَاضِیَ الْحَقِّ.\nO Generous pardoner, O Great Benefactor, O Abounding Effecter of goodness, O Foremost Superabundant, O Ever Kind, O Subtle Maker, O Reliever of pain, O Supplementer of damage, O Lord of the realm, O The Just Judge.\n(35) To Cure Toothache\nYAA MAN HOWA FEE A’HDEHI WAFIYYUN, YAA MAN HOWA FEE WAFAA-E’HI QAWIYYUN YAA MAN HOWA FEE QUWWATEHI A’LIYYUN, YAA MAN HOWA FEE OLUWWEHI QAREEBUN, YAA MAN HOWA FEE QURBEHI LATEEFUN, YAA MAN HOWA FEE LUTFEHI SHAREEFUN, YAA MAN HOWA FEE SHARAFEHI A’ZEEZUN YAA MAN HOWA FEE I’ZZEHI A’ZEEMUN, YAA MAN HOWA FEE A’ZAMATEHI MAJEEDUN, YAA MAN HOWA FEE MAJEEDEHI HAMEEDUN.\nیَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ عَہْدِہٖ وَ فِیٌّ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ وَفَآئِہٖ قَوِیٌّ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ قُوَّتِہٖ عَلِیٌّ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ عُلُوِّہٖ قَرِیْبٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ قُرْبِہٖ لَطِیْفٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ لُطْفِہٖ شَرِیْفٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ شَرَفِہٖ عَزِیْزٌ يَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ عِزِّہٖ عَظِیْمٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ عَظَمَتِہٖ مَجِیْدٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ مَجْدِہٖ حَمِیْدٌ.\nO He Who keeps His word sincerely, O He Who is strong in sincerity, O He Who is High in strength, O He Who is High in strength, O He Who is Near in highness, O He Who is Subtle in nearness, O He Who is Noble in Subtility, O He Who is Mighty in nobility, O He Who is Great in might, O He Who is Glorious in greatness, O He Who is praiseworthy in glory.\n(36) To Seek Protection Against Jinn\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA, YAA KAAFEE, YAA SHAAFEE, YAA WAAFEE YAA MO-A’AFEE, YAA HAADEE, YAA DAAE’E, YAA QAAZEE, YAA RAAZEE, YAA A’ALEE, YAA BAAQEE.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَا کَافِیْ یَا شَافِیْ یَا وَافِیْ یَا مُعَافِیْ یَا ہَادِیْ یَا دَاعِیْ يَا قَاضِیْ یَا رَاضِیْ یَا عَالِیْ یَا بَاقِیْ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O Adequate, O Curer, O Fulfiller, O Acquitter, O Shower of the right path, O Summoner, O Judge, O Consentient, O High, O Survivor.\n(37) To Win Battle\nYAA MAN KULLO SHAY-IN KHAAZEO’ON LAHU, YAA MAN KULLO SHAY-IN KHAASHEO’ON LAHU, YAA MAN KULLO SHAY-IN KAA-E’NUN LAHU, YAA MAN KULLO SHAY-IN MAWJOODUN LAHU, YAA MAN KULLO SHAY-IN MONEEBUN ELAYHE, YAA MAN KULLO SHAY-IN KHAA-E’FUN MINHO, YAA MAN KULLO SHAY-IN QAA-E’MUN BEHI, YAA MAN KULLO SHAY-IN SAA-E’RUN ELAYHE YAA MAN KULLO SHAY-IN YOSABBEHO BE-HAMDEHI, YAA MAN KULLO SHAY-IN HAALEKUN ILLAA WAJHOHU.\nیَا مَنْ کُلُّ شَیْءٍ خَاضِعٌ لَہٗ یَا مَنْ کُلُّ شَیْءٍ خَاشِعٌ لَہٗ یَا مَنْ کُلُّ شَیْءٍ کَآئِنٌ لَہٗ یَا مَنْ کُلُّ شَیْءٍ مَّوْجُوْدٌ بِہٖ یَا مَنْ کُلُّ شَیْءٍ مُنِیْبٌ اِلَیْہِ یَا مَنْ کُلُّ شَیْءٍ خَآئِفٌ مِنْہُ یَا مَنْ کُلُّ شَیْءٍ قَآئِمٌ بِہٖ یَا مَنْ کُلُّ شَیْءٍ صَآئِرٌ اِلَیْہِ یَا مَنْ کُلُّ شَیْءٍ یُسَبِّحُ بِحَمْدِہٖ یَا مَنْ کُلُّ شَیْءٍ ہَالِکٌ اِلَّا وَجْہَہٗ.\nO He to Whom all things bow down, O He to Whom all things submit, O He for Whom all things persevere, O He for Whom all things exist, O He towards Whom all things turn to, O He! All things are afraid of Whom, O He because of Whom all things endure, O He towards Whom all things draw near, O He Whom all things glorify with praise, O He except Who all things die.\n(38) To Seek Allah’s Help \nYAA MAN LAA MAFARRA ILLAA ELAYHE, YAA MAN LAA MAFZA-A’ ILLAA ELAYHE, YAA MAN LAA MAQSADA ILLAA ELAYHE, YAA MAN LA MANJA MINHO ILLAA ELAYHE, YAA MAN LA YARGHABO ILLAA ELAYHE, YA MAN LA HAWLA WA LAA QUWWATA ILLAA BEHI, YAA MAN LA YUSTA-A’ANO ILLAA BEHI, YAA MAN LAA YATAWAKKALO ILLAA A’LAIHE, YAA MAN LAA YURJAA ILLAA HOWA, YAA MAN LA YA’BODO ILLAA HOWA.\nیَا مَنْ لَا مَفَرَّ اِلَّا اِلَیْہِ یَا مَنْ لَا مَفْزَعَ اِلَّا اِلَیْہِ یَا مَنْ لَا مَقْصَدَ اِلَّا اِلَیْہِ یَا مَنْ لَا مَنْجٰی مِنْہُ اِلَّا اِلَیْہِ یَا مَنْ لَا یُرْغَبُ اِلَّا اِلَیْہِ یَا مَنْ لَا حَوْلَ وَ لَا قُوَّۃَ اِلَّا بِہٖ یَا مَنْ لَا یُسْتَعَانُ اِلَّا بِہٖ یَا مَنْ لَا یَتَوَکَّلُ اِلَّا عَلَیْہِ یَا مَنْ لَا یُرْجٰی اِلَّا ہُوَ یَا مَنْ لَا یُعْبَدُ اِلَّا اِیَّا ہُوَ.\nO He aside from Whom there is no asylum, O He aside from Whom there is no refuge, O He aside from Whom there is no destination, O he aside from Whom there is no place of escape, O He aside from Whom there is no one to lean upon, O He Who alone, and no one else, has power and might, O He Who alone, and no one else, is called upon for help, O He Who alone, and no one else, is relied upon, O He Who alone, and no one else, is hope¬fully looked forward to, O He Who alone, and no one else, is worshipped.\n(39) To Overwhelm The Enemy \nYAA KHAYRAL MARHOOBEENA, YAA KHAYRAL MARGHOOBEENA, YAA KHAYRAL MATLOOBEENA YA KHAYRAL MAS-OOLEENA, YAA KHAYRAL MAQSOODEENA, YAA KHAYRAL MAZKOOREENA, YAA KHAYRAL MASHKOOREENA, YAA KHAYRAL MAHBOOBEENA, YAA KHAYRAL MAD-O’OWEENA, YAA KHAYRAL MOOSTAA-NESEENA.\nیَا خَیْرَ الْمَرْہُوْبِیْنَ یَا خَیْرَ الْمَرْغُوْبِیْنَ یَا خَیْرَ الْمَطْلُوْبِیْنَ یَا خَیْرَ الْمَسْئُوْلِیْنَ یَا خَیْرَ الْمَقْصُوْدِیْنَ یَا خَیْرَ الْمَذْکُوْرِیْنَ یَا خَیْرَ الْمَشْکُوْرِیْنَ یَا خَیْرَ الْمَحْبُوْبِیْنَ یَا خَیْرَ الْمَدْعُوِّیْنَ یَا خَیْرَ الْمُسْتَأنِسِیْنَ.\nO The Best of those (who are) feared, O The Best of those (who are) held dear, O The Best of those (who are) sought after, O The Best of those (who are) besought, O The Best of those (who are) longed for, O The Best of those (who are) remem¬bered, O The Best of those (who are) thankfully acknowledged, O The Best of those (who are) adored, O The Best of those (who are) called upon, O The Best of those (who are) befriended.\n(40) To Seek Forgiveness \nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA, YAA GHAAFERO, YAA SAATERO, YAA QAADERO, YAA QAAHERO, YAA FAATERO, YAA KAASERO, YAA JAABERO, YAA ZAAKERO, YAA NAAZERO, YAA NAASERO.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَا غَافِرُ یَا سَاتِرُ یَا قَادِرُ یَا قَاہِرُ یَا فَاطِرُ یَا کَاسِرُ یَاجَابِرُ یَا ذَاکِرُ یَا نَاظِرُ یَا نَاصِرُ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O Absolver, O Coverer, O Absolute, O Victor, O Maker, O Wrecker, O Assembler, O Relater, O Onlooker, O Succourer.\n(41) To Disperse Hot Poisonous Winds\nYAA MAN KHALAQA FASAWWAA, YAA MAN QADDARA FAHADAA, YAA MAYN YAKSHEFUL BALWAA, YAA MAYN YASMA-U’N NAJWAA, YAA MAYN YUNQEZUL GHARQAA, YAA MAYN YUNJIL HALKAA, YAA MAYN YASHFIL MARZA YAA MAN AZHAKA WA ABKAA, YAA MAN AMAATA WA AHYAA YAA MAN KHALAQAZ ZAWJAYNAZ ZAKARA WAL UNSAA.\nیَا مَنْ خَلَقَ فَسَوّٰی یَا مَنْ قَدَّرَ فَہَدٰی یَا مَنْ یَّکْشِفُ الْبَلْوٰی یَا مَنْ یَسْمَعُ النَّجْوٰی یَا مَنْ یُنْقِدُ الْغَرْقٰی یَا مَنْ یُنْجِیَ الْہَلْکٰی یَا مَنْ یَّشْفِی الْمَرْضٰی یَا مَنْ اَضْحَکَ وَ اَبْکٰی یَا مَنْ اَمَاتَ وَ اَحْیٰی یَا مَنْ خَلَقَ الزَّوجَیْنِ الذَّکَرَ وَالْاُنْثٰی.\nO He Who created and arranged (the creation) systematically, O He Who made laws and (thus) showed the right path, O He Who disperses calam¬ities, O He Who hears the whispering secrets, O He Who comes to the rescue of those who have been overwhelmed, O He Who saves from the danger of annihilation, O He Who cures the sick, O He Who brings about happiness and grief, O He Who puts to death and brings to life, O He Who created pairs, male and female.\n(42) To Seek Safeguard Against Calamities\nYAA MAN FIL-BARRE WAL-BAHRE SABEELOHU YAA MAN FIL-AAFAAQE AAYAATOHU, YAA MAN FIL-AAYAATE BURHAANOHU, YAA MAN FIL-MAMAATE QUDRATOHU YAA MAN FIL-QOBOORE I’BRATOHU, YAA MAN FIL-QAYAAMATE MOLKOHU, YAA MAN FIL-HESAABE HAYBATOHU, YAA MAN FIL-MEEZAANE QAZAA-OHU, YAA MAN FIL-JANNATE SAWAABOHU, YAA MAN FINNAARE E’QAABOHU.\nیَا مَنْ فِی الْبَرِّ وَالْبَحْرِ سَبِیْلُہٗ یَا مَنْ فِیْ الْآفَاقِ اٰیٰتُہٗ یَا مَنْ فِی الْاٰیَاتِ بُرْہَانُہٗ یَا مَنْ فِی الْمَمَاتِ قُدْرَتُہٗ یَا مَنْ فِی الْقُبُوْرِ عِبْرَتُہٗ یَا مَنْ فِی الْقِیٰمَۃِ مُلْکُہٗ یَا مَنْ فِی الْحِسَابِ ہَیْبَتُہٗ یَا مَنْ فِی الْمِیْزَانِ قَضَآؤُہٗ یَا مَنْ فِی الْجَنَّۃِ ثَوَابُہٗ یَا مَنْ فِی النَّارِ عِقَابُہٗ.\nO He Who has means and ways on the land and in the seas, O He Whose signs are visible all over the universe, O He Whose signs are clear argu¬ments, O He Who controls through mortality, O He Who makes graves draw attention to His warn¬ing, O He Who owns the Day of Resurrection, O He Who overawes through the Day of reckoning, O He Who passes judgment after scaling (good and bad), O He Who awards paradise as reward, O He Who condemns to Hell as a punishment.\n(43) To Have The Patronage Of The Wealthy\nYAA MAN ELAYHE YAHREBUL KHAAEFOONA, YAA MAN ELAYHE YAFZA-U’L MUZNEBOONA, YAA MAN ELAYHE YAQSADUL MONEEBOONA YAA MAN ELAYHE YARGHABUZ ZAAHEDOONA, YAA MAN ELAYHE YALJAUL MOTAHAYYEROONA, YAA MAN BEHI YASTAANESUL MOREEDOONA, YAA MAN BEHI YAFTAKHERUL MOHIBBOONA, YAA MAN FEE A’FVEHI YATMA-U’L KHAATE-OONA, YAA MAN ELAYHE YASKONUL MOOQENOONA, YAA MAN ELAYHE YATAWAKKALUL MOTAWAKKELOONA.\nیَا مَنْ اِلَیْہِ یَہْرَبُ الْخَآئِفُوْنُ یَا مَنْ اِلَیْہِ یَفْزَعُ الْمُذْنِبُوْنُ یَا مَنْ اِلَیْہِ یَقْصِدُ الْمُنِیْبُوْنَ یَا مَنْ اِلَیْہِ یَرْغَبُ الزَّاہِدُوْنُ یَا مَنْ اِلَیْہِ یَلْجَاءُ الْمُتَحَیِّرُوْنَ یَا مَنْ بِہٖ یَسْتَاْنِسُ الْمُرِیْدُوْنُ یَا مَنْ بِہٖ یَفْتَخِرُ الْمُحِبُّوْنُ یَا مَنْ فِی عَفْوِہٖ یَطْمَعُ الْخَاطِئُوْنَ یَا مَنْ اِلَیْہِ یَسْکُنُ الْمُوْقِنُوْنَ یَا مَنْ عَلَیْہِ یَتَوَکَّلُ الْمُتَوَکِّلُوْنَ.\nO He towards Who run the frightened, O He towards Whom flee the sinners (for help), O He towards Whom move the repentant, O He to Whom turn the pious, O He with Whom the bewildered take refuge, O He with Whom the entirely devoted become familiar, O He of Whom the lovers are proud, O He Whose forgiveness the transgressors long for, O He in Whom the believ¬ers find peace, O He upon Whom the trusting rely.\n(44) To Cultivate Love And Friendship\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA, YAA HABEEBO, YAA TABEEBO, YAA QAREEBO, YAA RAQEEBO, YAA HASEEBO, YAA MOHEEBO YAA MOSEEBO, YAA MOJEEBO, YAA KHABEERO, YAA BASEERO.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَا حَبِیْبُ یَا طَبِیْبُ یَا قَرِیْبُ یَا رَقِیْبُ یَا حَسِیْبُ یَا مُہِیْبُ یَا مُثِیْبُ یَا مُجِیْبُ یَا خَبِیْرُ یَا بَصِیْرُ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O Friend, O Doctor, O Near, O Preserver, O Reckoner, O Awe-Inspiring, O Requiter, O Hearer of prayers, O All-Knowing, O All-Seeing. \n(45) To Get Rid Of Fearful Dreams \nYAA AQRABA MIN KULLE QAREEBIN, YAA AHABBA MIN KULLE HABEEBIN, YAA ABSARA MIN KULLE BASEERIN YAA AKHBARA MIN KULLE KHABEERIN, YAA ASHRAFA MIN KULLE SHAREEFIN, YAA ARFA-A’ MIN KULLE RAFEE-I’N, YAA AQWAA MIN KULLE QAWIYYIN, YAA AGHNA MIN KULLE GHANIYYIN, YAA AJWADA MIN KULLE JAWAADIN, YAA AR-A’FA MIN KULLE RA-O’OFIN.\nیَآ اَقْرَبَ مِنْ کُلِّ قَرِیْبٍ یَآ اَحَبَّ مَنْ کُلَّ حَبِیْبٍ یَآ اَبْصَرَ مِنْ کُلِّ بَصِیْرٍ یَآ اَخْبَرَ مِنْ کُلِّ خَبِیْرٍ یَآ اَشْرَفَ مِنْ کُلِّ شَرِیْفٍ یَآ اَرْفَعَ مِنْ کُلِّ رَفِیْعِ یَا اَقْوٰی مِنْ کُلِّ قَوِیٍّ یَآ اَغْنٰی مِنْ کُلِّ غَنِیٍّ یَآ اَجْوَدَ مِنْ کُلِّ جَوَادٍ یَآ اَرْئَفَ مِنْ کُلِّ رَءُوْفٍ.\nO The Nearest of all nears, OThe Dearest of all dears, O The Most Discerning of all discerners, O The Most Aware of all well-informed, O The Noblest of all nobles, O The Most Exalted of all exalted, O The Mightiest of all powerfuls, O The Most Independent of all independents, O The Most Generous of all bountifuls, O The Most Compas¬sionate of all pardoners.\n(46) To Cure Infantile Paralysis\nYAA GHAALEBAN GHAYRA MAGHLOOBIN, YAA SAANE-A’N GHAYRA MASNOO-I’N, YAA KHAALEQAN GHAYRA MAKHLOOQIN, YAA MAALEKAN GHAYRA MAMLOOKIN, YAA QAHERAN GHAYRA MAQHOORIN, YAA RAAFE-A’N GHAYRA MARFOO-I’N YAA HAAFEZAN GHAYRA MAHFOOZIN, YAA NAASERAN GHAYRA MANSOORIN YAA SHAAHEDAN GHAYRA GHAA-EBIN, YAA QAREEBAN GHAYRA BA-E’EDIN.\nیَا غَالِبًا غَیْرَ مَغْلُوْبٍ یَا صَانِعًا غَیْرَ مَصْنُوْعٍ یَا خَالِقًا غَیْرَ مَخْلُوْقٍ یَا مَالِکًا غَیْرَ مَمْلُوْکٍ یَا قَاہِرًا غَیْرَ مَقْہُوْرٍ یَا رَافِعًا غَیْرَ مَرْفَوْعٍ یَا حَافِظًا غَیْرَ مَحْفُوْظٍ یَا نَاصِرًا غَیْرَ مَنْصُوْرٍ یَا شَاہِدًا غَیْرَ غَآئِبٍ یَا قَرِیْبًا غَیْرَ بَعِیْدٍ.\nO Conqueror (Who is) not conquered, O Mak¬er (Who is) not made, O Creator (Who is) not created, O Owner (Who is) not owned, O Subduer (Who is) not subdued, O Raiser (Who is) not raised, O Guardian (Who is) not guarded, O Helper (Who is) not helped, O Present (Who is) not absent, O Near (Who is) not away.\n(47) To Cure Epilepsy\nYAA NOORAN NOORE, YAA MOONAWWARAN NOORE, YAA KHAALEQAN NOORE, YAA MODABBERAN NOORE, YAA MOQADDERAN NOORE, YAA NOORA KULLE NOORIN, YAA NOORAN QABLA KULLE NOORIN, YAA NOORAN BA’DA KULLE NOORIN, YAA NOORAN FAWQA KULLE NOORIN, YAA NOORAN LAYSA KAMISLEHI NOORUN.\nیَا نُوْرَ النُّوْرِ یَا مُنَوِّرَ النُّوْرِ یَا خَالِقَ النُّوْرِ یَا مُدَبِّرَ النُّوْرِ یَا مُقَدِّرًا النُّوْرِ یَا نُوْرَ کُلِّ نُوْرٍ یَا نُوْرًا قَبْلَ کُلِّ نُوْرٍ یَا نُوْرًا بَعْدَ کُلِّ نُوْرٍ یَا نُوْرًا فَوْقَ کُلِّ نُوْرٍ یَا نُوْرًا لَیْسَ کَمِثْلِہٖ نُوْرٌ.\nO Light and Light, O Illuminator of light, O Creator of light, O Director of Light, O Architect of light, O Light of every light, O Light prior to every light, O Light beyond every light, O Light superior to every light, O Light like of which there is no light.\n(48) To Get Rid Of Constipation\nYAA MAN A’TAA-OHU SHAREEFUN, YAA MAN FE’LOHU LATEEFUN, YAA MAN LUTFOHU MOQIMUN, YAA MAN EHSANOHU QADEEMUN, YAA MAN QAWLOHU HAQQUN, YAA MAN WA’DOHU SIDQOON, YAA MAN A’FWOHU FAZLUN, YAA MAN A’ZAABOHU A’DLUN, YAA MAN ZIKROHU HULVUN, YAA MAN FAZLOHU A’MEEMUN.\nیَا مَنْ عَطَآؤُہٗ شَرِیْفٌ یَا مَنْ فِعْلُہٗ لَطِیْفٌ یَا مَنْ لُطْفُہٗ مُقِیْمٌ یَا مَنْ اِحْسَانُہٗ قَدِیْمٌ یَاَ مَنْ قَوْلُہٗ حَقٌّ یَا مَنْ وَعْدُہٗ صِدْقٌ یَا مَنْ عَفْوُہٗ فَضْلٌ یَا مَنْ عَذَابُہٗ عَدْلٌ یَا مَنْ ذِکْرُہٗ حُلْوٌ یَا مَنْ فَضْلُہٗ عَمِیْمٌ.\nO He Whose gifts are excellent, O He Whose actions are subtle, O He Whose kindness is stable, O He Whose beneficence is eternal, O He Whose word is true, O He Whose promise is sincere, O He Whose pardon is complete, O He Whose punish¬ments is just, O He Whose remembrance is pleas¬ant, O He Whose bounties are for one and all. \n(49) To Cure Palpitation Of Heart\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA, YAA MOSAHHELO, YAA MOFAS-SELO, YAA MOBADDELO, YAA MOZALLELO, YAA MONAZZELO, YAA MONAWWELO, YAA MUFZELO, YAA MUJZELO, YAA MUMHELO, YAA MUJMELO.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَا مُسَہِّلُ یَا مُفَصِّلُ یَا مُبَدِّلُ یَا مُذَلِّلُ یَا مُنَزِّلُ یَا مُنَوِّلُ یَا مُفْضِلُ یَا مُجْزِلُ یَا مُمْہِلُ یَا مُجْمِلُ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O Simplifier, O Separator, O Compensator, O Tamer, O Hospitable, O Bestower of gifts, O Bounteous, O Distributor, O Granter of respite, O Gatherer.\n(50) To Improve Eye Sight\nYAA MAYN YARAA WA LA YORAA, YAA MAYN YAKHLOQO WA LAA YUKHLAQO, YAA MAYN YAHDE WA LAA YOHDAA YAA MAYN YOHYEE WA LAA YOHYAA, YAA MAYN YAS-ALO WA LAA YUS-ALO YAA MAYN YUT-E’MO WA LAA YUT-A’MO, YAA MAYN-YOJEERO WA LAA YOJAARO A’LAYHE, YAA MAYN YAQZE