ُہٗ یَا مَنْ یَّبْدَؤُ الْخَلْقَ ثُمَّ یُعِیْدُہٗ یَا مَنْ اِلَیْہِ یَرْجِعُ الْاَمْرُ کُلُّہٗ یَا مَنْ اَظْہَرَ فِی کُلِّ شَیْءٍ لُطْفَہٗ یَا مَنْ اَحْسَنَ کُلَّ شَیْءٍ خَلْقَہٗ یَا مَنْ تَصَرَّفَ فِی الْخَلَآئِقِ قُدْرَتُہٗ.\nO He Whose greatness spreads in all directions of the heavens, O He Whose signs are visible all over the earth, O He Whose arguments demon¬strate through all objects, O He Whose wonders abound in the rivers and oceans, O He Whose treasures are found in the mountains, O He Who starts the creation and thereupon repeats, O He to Whom are reverted all affairs, O He Whose favours are evident in everything, O He Who makes well whatever He creates, O He Who manages His creation with authority.\n(59) To Cure Stomach-Ache\nYAA HABEEBA MAN LAA HABEEBA LAHU, YAA TABEEBA MAN LAA TABEEBA LAHU, YAA MOJEEBA MAN LAA MOJEEBA LAHU, YAA SHAFEEQA MAN LAA SHAFEEQA LAHU, YAA RAFEEQA MAN-LAA RAFIQA LAHU, YAA MOGHEESA MAN LA MOGHEESA LAHU, YAA DALEELA MAN LAA DALEELA LAHU, YAA ANEESA MAN LAA ANEESA LAHU, YAA RAAHEMA MAN LAA RAAHEMA LAHU, YAA SAAHEBA MAN LAA SAAHEBA LAHU.\nیَا حَبِیْبَ مَنْ لَّا حَبِیْبَ لَہٗ یَا طَبِیْبَ مَنْ لَّا طَبِیْبَ لَہٗ یَا مُجِیْبَ مَنْ لَّا مُجِیْبَ لَہٗ یَا شَفِیْقَ مَنْ لَّا شَفِیْقَ لَہٗ یَا رَفِیْقَ مَنْ لَّا رَفِیْقَ لَہٗ یَا مُغِیْثَ مَنْ لَّا مُغِیْثَ لَہٗ یَا دَلِیْلَ مَنْ لَّا دَلِیْلَ لَہٗ یَا اَنِیْسَ مَنْ لَّا اَنِیْسَ لَہٗ یَا رَاحِمَ مَنْ لَّا رَاحِمَ لَہٗ یَا صَاحِبَ مَنْ لَّا صَاحِبَ لَہٗ.\nO Friend of him who is friendless, O Curer of him who has no physician, O Answerer of him who has no responder, O Patron of him who has no sympathizer, O Companion of him who has no comrade, O Helper of him who is helpless, O Guide of him who has no indication, O Confidant of him who has no associate, O Commiserator of him who has no pitier, O Escort of him who has no colleague.\n(60) To Succeed In Vital Undertakings\nYAA KAAFEYA MANIS TAKFAAHO, YAA HADEYA MANIS TAHDAAHO, YAA KAALEYA MANIS TAKLAAHO, YA RAA-E’YA MANIS TARA’AHO, YAA SHAFEY