ارَ یَا مَنْ خَلَقَ الظِّلَ وَالْحَرُوْرَ یَا مَنْ سَخَّرَ الشَّمْسَ وَالْقَمَرَ یَا مَنْ قَدَّرَ الْخَیْرَ وَالشَّرَّ یَا مَنْ خَلَقَ الْمَوْتَ وَالْحَیٰوۃَ یَا مَنْ لَّہُ الْخَلْقُ وَالْاَمْرُ یَا مَنْ لَّمْ یَتَّخِذْ صَاحِبَۃً وَّ لَا وَلَدًا یَا مَنْ لَیْسَ لَہٗ شَرِیْکٌ فِی الْمُلْکِ یَا مَنْ لَّمْ یَکُنْ لَّہٗ وَلِیٌّ مِنَ الذُّلِّ.\nO He Who interchanges night and day, O He Who created light and darkness, O He Who created shade and warmth, O He Who keeps in line the sun and the moon, O He Who takes account of good and evil, O He Who brings about life and death, O He to Whom belong creation and com¬mand, O He Who does not take up wife or child, O He Who shares with no one in exercise of author¬ity, O He Who does not choose friend from among the vulgar.\n(63) To Make Profit In Business\nYAA MAYN YA’LAMO MORAADAL MOREEDEENA, YAA MAYN YA’LAMO ZAMEERAS SAAMETEENA, YAA MAYN YASMA-O ANEENAL WAAHENEENA, YAA MAYN YARAA BOKAA-AL KHAA-EFEENA, YAA MAYN YAMLEKO HAWAA-EJAS SAA-ELEENA, YAA MAYN YAQBALO OOZRAT TAA-EBEENA, YAA MAN LAA YUSLEHO A’MALAL MUFSEDEENA, YAA MAN LAA YOZEE-O AJRAL MOHSENEENA YAA MAN LAA YAB-O’DO A’N QOLOOBIL A’AREFEENA, YAA AJWADAL AJWADEENA.\nیَا مَنْ یَّعْلَمُ مُرَادُ الْمُرِیْدِیْنَ یَا مَنْ یَّعْلَمُ ضَمِیْرَ الصَّامِتِیْنَ یَا مَنْ یَّسْمَعُ اَنِیْنَ الْوَاہِنِیْنَ یَا مَنْ یَّرٰی بُکَآءَ الْخَآئِفِیْنَ یَا مَنْ یَّمْلِکُ حَوَآئِجَ السَّآئِلِیْنَ یَا مَنْ یَقْبَلُ عُذْرَ التَّآئِبِیْنَ یَا مَنْ لَا یُصْلِحُ اَعْمَالَ الْمُفْسِدِیْنَ یَا مَنْ لَا یُضِیْعَ اَجْرَ الْمُحْسِنِیْنَ یَا مَنْ لَا یَبْعُدُ عَنْ قُلُوْبِ الْعَارِفِیْنَ یَا اَجْوَدَ الْاَجْوَدِیْنَ.\nO He Who is aware of the desire of the hopeful, O He Who is aware of the mind of the silent, O He Who hears the groanings of the weak, O He Who takes notice of the crying of the afraid, O He Who meets the demands of the needy, O He Who accepts the excuse of the repentant, O He Who does not make better the ways of the mischievous, O He Who does not let go waste the reward of the praiseworthy, O He Who is not far away from the hearts of the intelligent, O The Most Generous of all generous.\n(64) To Cure Splitting Headache\nYAA DAA-E’MAL BAQAA-E, YAA SAAME-A’D DOAA-E, YAA WAASE-A’L ATAA-E, YAA GAAFERAL KHATAAYAA YAA BADI-A’S SAMAA-E, YAA HUSNAL BALAA-E, YAA JAMEELAS SANAA-E, YAA QADEEMAS SANAA-E, YAA KASEERAL WAFAA-E, YAA SHAREEFAL JAZAA-E.\nیَا دَآئِمَ الْبَقَآءِ یَا سَامِعَ الدُّعَآءِ یَا وَاسِعَ الْعَطَاءِ یَا غَافِرَ الْخَطَآءِ یَا بَدِیْعَ السَّمَاءِ یَا حَسَنَ الْبَلَآءِ یَا جَمِیْلَ الثَّنَآءِ یَا قَدِیْمَ السَّنَآءِ یَا کَثِیْرَ الْوَفَآءِ یَا شَرِیْفَ الْجَزَآءِ.\nO Continuous Ever-lasting, O Listener of invo¬cations, O Liberal Bestower, O Absolver of transgressions, O Establisher of sky, O Skilful Tester, O Excellent Praiser, O Eternally Sublime, O Lib¬eral Fulfiller, O Noble Rewarder.\n(65) To Seek Forgiveness Of Sins\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA, YAA SATTAARO YAA GHAFFAARO, YAA QAHHAARO, YAA JABBAARO, YAA SABBAARO, YAA BAARRO YAA MUKHTAARO, YAA FATTAAHO, YAA NAFFAAHO, YAA MURTAAHO.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَا سَتَّارُ یَا غَفَّارُ یَا قَہَّارُ یَا جَبَّارُ یَا صَبَّارُ یَا بَآرُّ یَا مُخْتَارُ یَا فَتَّاحُ یَا نَفَّاحُ یَا مُرْتَاحُ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O very Forgiving, O Who covers (sins), O Who wields power, O Who puts in force (laws) O Who endures calmly, O Who acts well, O Who exercises free will, O Who takes into possession, O Who moves (winds), O Who gives comfort.\n(66) To Get Rid Of Poverty\nYAA MAN KHALAQANEE WA SAWWAANEE, YAA MAN RAZAQANEE WA RABBAANEE, YAA MAN AT-A’MANEE WA SAQAANEE, YAA MAN QARRABANEE WA ADNAANEE, YAA MAN A’SAMANEE WA KAFAANEE, YAA MAN HAFAZANEE WA KALAANEE, YAA MAN A-A’ZZANEE WA AGHNAANEE, YAA MAN WAQAFANEE WA HADAANEE, YAA MAN AANASANEE WA AAWAANEE, YAA MAN AMAATANEE WA AHYAANEE.\nیَا مَنْ خَلَقَنِیْ وَ سَوَّانِیْ یَا مَنْ رَزَقَنِیْ وَ رَبَّانِیْ یَا مَنْ اَطْعَمَنِیْ وَ سَقَانِیْ یَا مَنْ قَرَّبَنِیْ وَ اَدْنَانِیْ یَا مَنْ عَصَمَنِیْ وَ کَفَانِیْ یَا مَنْ حَفِظَنِیْ وَ کَلَانِیْ یَا مَنْ اَعَزَّنِیْ وَ اَغْنَانِیْ یَا مَنْ وَفَّقَنِیْ وَ ہَدَانِیْ یَا مَنْ اٰنَسَنِیْ وَ اٰوَانِیْ یَا مَنْ اَمَاتَنِیْ وَ اَحْیَانِیْ.\nO He Who created me and shaped me well, O He Who gave sustenance and put me in good order, O He Who fed me and arranged water for me, O He Who kept me near and gave me wisdom, O He Who preserved me and defended me, O He Who protected me and kept me safe, O He Who paid attention to me and made me well-to-do, O He Who perfected me and showed me the right path, O He Who became familiar with me and received me gladly, O He Who puts me to death and brings me to life.\n(67) To Cure Eye Ailments\nYAA MAYN YOHIQQUL HAQQA BE-KALEMAATEHI, YAA MAYN YAQBALAT TAWBATA A’N E’BAADEHI, YAA MAYN YAHOOLO BAYNAL MAR-E WA QALBEHI, YAA MAN LAA TANFA-O’SH SHAFAA-A’TA ILLAA BE-IZNEHI, YAA MAN HOWA A’LAMO BE-MAN ZALLA A’N SABEELEHI, YAA MAN-LA MO’AQ-QEBA LE-HUKMEHI, YAA MAN-LAA RAADDAA LE-QAZAA-EHI, YAA MANIN QAADA KULLO SHAY-IN LE-AMREHI, YAA MANIS-SAMAAWAATO MATWIYYAATUN BE-YAMEENEHI, YAA MAYN YURSELUR REYAAHA BUSHRAN BAYNA YADAY RAHMATEHI.\nیَا مَنْ یُّحِقُّ الْحَقَّ بِکَلِمَاتِہٖ یَا مَنْ یَّقْبَلُ التَّوْبَۃَ عَنْ عِبَادِہٖ یَا مَنْ یَّحُوْلُ بَیْنَ الْمَرْءِ وَ قَلْبِہٖ یَا مَنْ لَّا تَنْفَعُ الشَّفَاعَۃُ اِلَّا بِاِذْنِہٖ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ اَعْلَمُ بِمَنْ ضَلَّ عَنْ سَبِیْلِہٖ یَا مَنْ لَّا مُعَقِّبَ لِحُکْمِہٖ یَا مَنْ لَّا رَآدَّ لِقَضَآئِہٖ یَا مَنِ انْقَادَ کُلُّ شَیْءٍ لِّاَمْرِہٖ یَا مَنِ السَّمٰوٰتُ مَطْوِیَّاتٌ بِیَمِیْنِہٖ یَا مَنْ یُّرْسِلُ الرِّیَاحَ بُشْرًا بَیْنَ یَدَیْ رَحْمَتِہٖ.\nO He Who confirms truth by His words, O He Who corresponds to the repentance of his servants of His servants, O He Who intervenes between man and his soul, O He Who does not take notice ‘ of any intercession unless by His leave, O He Who is well aware of him who abandons the right path ‘ and goes astray, O He Whose command no one can criticize, O He Whose proclamation no one can revoke, O He Whose Directions everyone follows, O He under Whose control the skies extend across, O He Who sends winds as harbinger of glad-tidings through His mercy.\n(68) To Ward Off Plague\nYAA MAN JA-A’LAL ARZA MEHAADAN, YAA MAN JA-A’LAL JEBAALA AWTADAN, YAA MAN JA-A’LASH SHAMSA SERAAJAN, YAA MAN JA-A’LAL QAMARA NOORAN, YAA MAN JA-A’LAL LAYLA LEBAASAN, YAA MAN JA-A’LAN NAHAARA MA-A’ASHAN, YAA MAN JA-A’LAN NAWMA SOBAATAN, YAA MAN JA-A’LAS SAMAA-A BENAA-AN, YAA MAN JA-A’LAL ASHYAA-A AZWAAJAN YAA MAN JA-ALAN NAARA MIRSAADAN.\nیَا مَنْ جَعَلَ الْاَرْضَ مِہَادًا یَا مَنْ جَعَلَ الْجِبَالَ اَوْتَادًا یَا مَنْ جَعَلَ الشَّمْسَ سِرَاجًا یَا مَنْ جَعَلَ الْقَمَرَ نُوْرًا یَا مَنْ جَعَلَ اللَّیْلَ لِبَاسًا یَا مَنْ جَعَلَ النَّہَارَ مَعَاشًا یَا مَنْ جَعَلَ النَّوْمَ سُبَاتًا یَا مَنْ جَعَلَ السَّمَآءَ بِنَآءً یَا مَنْ جَعَلَ الْاَشْیَآءَ اَزْوَاجًا یَا مَنْ جَعَلَ النَّارَ مِرْصَادًا.\nO He Who has made the earth like a spread out surface, O He Who has rammed in the mountains like pegs, O He Who has adorned the sun like a chandelier, O He Who has lit up to moon like a luminary, O He Who has created the night as a covering, O He Who has created the day to act and procure livelihood, O He Who has appointed the sleep for rest, O He Who has established the sky like an arch, O He Who has created pairs of all kind (of living creatures), O He Who has made Hell an ambush (for infidels).\n(69) To Achieve Eminence\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA, YAA SAMEE-O YAA SHAFEE-O’, YAA RAFEE-O’, YAA MANEE-O’, YAA SAREE-O’, YAA BADEE-O’, YAA KABEERO, YAA QADEERO, YAA KHABEERO, YAA MOJEERO.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَا سَمِیْعُ یَا شَفِیْعُ یَا رَفِیْعُ یَا مَنِیْعُ یَا سَرِیْعُ یَا بَدِیْعُ یَا کَبِیْرُ یَا قَدِیْرُ یَا خَبِیْرُ یَا مُجِیْرُ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O Who hears, O Who accepts intercession O Who bestows ranks, O Who prohibits, O Who is swift, O Who originates, O Who is powerful O Who is omnipo¬tent, O Who is well-informed, O Who gives sup¬port.\n(70) To Get Long Life\nYAA HAYYAN QABLA KULLE HAYYIN, YAA HAYYAN BA’DA KULLE HAYYIN YAA HAYYUL LAZEE LAYSA KAMISLEHI HAYYUN, YAA HAYYOOL LAZEE LAYSA YOSHAAREKOHU HAYYUN, YAA HAYYUL LAZEE LAA YAHTAAJO ILLA HAYYIN, YAA HAYYUL LAZEE YOMEETO KULLA HAYYIN, YAA HAYYUL-LAZEE YARZOQO KULLA HAYYIN, YAA HAYYAN LAM YARESIL HAYAATA MIN HAYYIN, YAA HAYYUL LAZEE YOHYIL MAWTA YAA HAYYO, YAA QAYYOOMO LA TAAKHOZOHU SENATUN WA LAA NAWM.\nیَا حَیًّا قَبْلَ کُلِّ حَیٍّ یَا حَیًّا بَعْدَ کُلِّ حَیٍّ یَا حَیُّ الَّذِیْ لَیْسَ کَمِثْلِہٖ حَیٌّ یَا حَیُّ الَّذِیْ لَا یُشَارِکُہٗ حَیٌّ یَا حَیُّ الَّذِیْ لَا یَحْتَاجُ اِلٰی حَیٍّ یَا حَیُّ الَّذِیْ یُمِیْتُ کُلَّ حَیٍّ یَا حَیُّ الَّذِیْ یَرْزُقُ کُلَّ حَیٍّ یَا حَیًّا لَمْ یَرِثِ الْحَیٰوۃَ مِنْ حَيٍّ یَا حَیُّ الَّذِیْ یُحْیِ الْمَوْتٰی یَا حَیُّ یَا قَیُّوْمُ لَا تَاْخُذُہٗ سِنَۃٌ وَّلاَ نَوْمٌ.\nO (uncaused) Living, ahead of all life, O Alive (eternally), beyond all life, O (Ever) Living like unto Whom there is no being, O (Ever) Living with Whom no (kept alive) partner is associated, O (Ever) Living Who turns not to any (kept alive) being, O (Ever) Living Who puts every living being to death, O (Ever) Living Who did not receive life from any being, O (Ever) Living Who gives livelihood to all living beings, O (Ever) Living Who has kept death operative, O (Ever) Living, O Ever-Lasting, Slumber seizes Him not, nor sleep.\n(71) To Prevent Cyclone\nYAA MAN LAHU ZIKRUN LAA YUNSAA YAA MAN LAHU NOORUN LAA YUTFAA, YAA MAN LAHU NE’AMUL LAA TOA’DDO, YAA MAN LAHU MULKUN LAA YAZOOLO, YAA MAN LAHU SANAA-U’L LAA YOHSAA, YAA MAN LAHU JALAALUL LAA YOKAYYAFO, YAA MAN LAHU KAMALUL LAA YUDRAKO, YAA MAN LAHU QAZAA-UL LAA YORADDO, YAA MAN LAHU SEFAATUL LAA TOBADDALO, YAA MAN LAHU NO-O’OTUN LAA TOGHAYYARO.\nیَا مَنْ لَہٗ ذِکْرٌ لَا یُنْسٰی یَا مَنْ لَہٗ نُوْرٌ لَا یُطْفٰی یَا مَنْ لَہٗ نِعَمٌ لَا تُعَدُّ یَا مَنْ لَہٗ مُلْکٌ لَا یَزُوْلُ یَا مَنْ لَہٗ ثَنَآءٌ لَا یُحْصٰی یَا مَنْ لَہٗ جَلَالٌ لَا یُکَیَّفُ یَا مَنْ لَہٗ کَمَالٌ لَا یُدْرَکُ یَا مَنْ لَہٗ قَضَآءٌ لَا یُرَدُّ یَا مَنْ لَہٗ صِفَاتٌ لَا تُبَدَّلُ یَا مَنْ لَہٗ نُعُوْتٌ لَا تُغَیَّرُ.\nO He Whose mention (name) is never put off, O He Whose Light is never extinguished, O He Whose bounties are countless, O He Whose king¬dom does not wither away, O He Whose praise knows no bounds, O He Whose power never diminishes, O He Whose perfection is unperceivable, O He Whose decree is irrevocable, O He Whose attributes are not transposable, O He Whose praise never loses colour.\n(72) To Cure Pain In Breasts\nYAA RABBAL A’ALAMEENA, YAA MAALEKA YAWMIDDEENE, YAA GHAAYATAT TAALEBEENA, YAA ZAHRAL LAAJEENA, YAA MUDREKAL HAAREBEENA, YAA MAYN YOHIBBUS SAABEREENA, YAA MAYN YOHIBBUT TAWWAABEENA, YAA MAYN YOHIBBUL MOTATAHHEREENA, YAA MAYN YOHIBBUL MOHSENEENA, YAA MAN HOWA A’LAMO BIL-MOHTADEENA.\nیَا رَبَّ الْعٰلَمِیْنَ یَا مَالِکَ یَوْمِ الدِّیْنَ یَا غَایَۃَ الطَّالِبِیْنَ یَا ظَہْرَ اللَّاجِیْنَ یَا مُدْرِکَ الْہَارِبِیْنَ یَا مَنْ یُّحِبُّ الصَّابِرِیْنَ یَا مَنْ یُّحِبُّ التَّوَّابِیْنَ یَا مَنْ یُّحِبُّ الْمُتَطَہِّرِیْنَ یَا مَنْ یُّحِبُّ الْمَحْسِنِیْنَ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ اَعْلَمُ بِالْمُہْتَدِیْنَ.\nO Lord of the worlds, O Owner of the Day of Judgement, O Last Resort of those who strive for, O Support of those who have plunged into the deep, O Seizer of fugitives, O He Who loves those who endure without complaints, O He Who loves the repentants, O He Who loves the pure, O He Who loves the good, O He Who knows best about those who are on the right path.\n(73) To Cure Rheumatism\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA, YAA SHAFEEQO, YAA RAFEEQO, YAA HAFEEZO, YAA MOHEETO, YAA MOQEETO, YAA MOGHEESO, YAA MO-I’ZZO, YAA MOZILLO, YAA MUBDE’O, YAA MO-E’EDO.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَا شَفِیْقُ یَا رَفِیْقُ یَا حَفِیْظُ یَا مُحِیْطُ یَا مُقِیْتُ یَا مُغِیْثُ یَا مُعِزُّ یَا مُذِلُّ یَا مُبْدِءُ یَا مُعِیْدُ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O Solicitous, O Kind Friend, O Administrator, O Who surrounds, O Who gives sustenance, O Who comes to help, O Who confers honour, O Who subdues, O Who begins, O Who brings back.\n(74) To Have A Son\nYAA MAN HOWA AHADUN BELAA ZIDDIN, YAA MAN HOWA FARDUN BELA NIDDIN, YAA MAN HOWA SAMADUN BELAA A’YBIN, YAA MAN HOWA VITRUN BELAA KAYFIN, YAA MAN HOWA QAAZIN BELAA HAYFIN, YAA MAN HOWA RABBUN BELAA WAZEERIN, YAA MAN HOWA A’ZEEZUN BELAA ZULLIN, YAA MAN HOWA GHANIYYUN BELAA FAQEERIN, YAA MAN HOWA MALAKUN BELAA A’ZLIN, YAA MAN HOWA MAWSOOFUN BELAA SHABEEHIN.\nیَا مَنْ ہُوَ اَحَدٌ بِلاَ ضِدٍّ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فَرْدٌ بِلاَ نِدٍ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ صَمَدٌ بِلاَ عَیْبٍ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ وِتْرٌ بِلاَ کَیْفٍ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ قَاضٍ بِلاَ حَیْفٍ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ رَبٌّ بِلاَ وَزِیْرِ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ عَزِیْزٌ بِلاَ ذُلٍّ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ غَنِیٌّ بِلاَ فَقْرٍ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ مَلِکٌ بِلاَ عَزْلٍ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ مَوْصُوْفٌ بِلاَ شَبِیْہٍ.\nO He Who is single without a counterpart, O He Who is one without a rival, O He Who is free from all wants without a defect, O He Who is one and only without chaos, O He Who settles matters without oppression, O He Who rules without an assistant, O He Who is glorious without humilia¬tion, O He Who is self-sufficient without priva¬tion, O He Who masters without degrading (His Servants), O He Whose attributes are described without ascribing similarities.\n(75) To Achieve Honourable Position\nYAA MAN ZIKROHU SHARAFUN LIZ-ZAAKEREENA, YAA MAN SHUKROHU FAWZOON LISH-SHAAKEREENA, YAA MAN HAMDOHU I’ZZUN LIL-HAAMEDEENA, YAA MAN TA-A’TOHU NAJAATUN LIL-MOTEE-E’ENA, YAA MAN BAABOHU MAFTOOHUN LIT-TAALEBEENA, YAA MAN SABEELOHU WAAZEHUN LIL-MONEEBEENA, YAA MAN AAYAATOHU BURHANUN LIN-NAAZEREENA, YAA MAN KETAABOHU TAZKERATUN LIL-MUTTAQEENA, YAA MAN-RIZQOHU O’MOOMUN LIT-TAA-E-E’ENA WAL A’ASEENA, YAA MAN RAHMATOHU QAREEBUN MENAL MOHSENEENA.\nیَا مَنْ ذِکْرُہٗ شَرَفٌ لِّلذَّاکِرِیْنَ یَا مَنْ شُکْرُہٗ فَوْزٌ لِّلشَّاکِرِیْنَ یَا مَنْ حَمْدُہٗ عِزٌّ لِّلْحَامِدِیْنَ یَا مَنْ طَاعَتُہٗ نَجَاۃٌ لِّلْمُطِیْعِیْنَ یَا مَنْ بَابُہٗ مَفْتُوْحٌ لِّلْطَّالِبِیْنَ یَا مَنْ سَبِیْلُہٗ وَاضِحٌ لِّلْمُنِیْبِیْنَ یَا مَنْ اٰیَاتُہٗ بُرْہَانٌ لِّلنَّاظِرِیْنَ یَا مَنْ کِتَابُہٗ تَذْکِرَۃٌ لِّلْمُتَّقِیْنَ یَا مَنْ رِّزْقُہٗ عُمُومٌ لِّلطَّآئِعِیْنَ وَالْعَاصِیْنَ یَا مَنْ رَّحْمَتُہٗ قَرِیْبٌ مِّنَ الْمُحْسِنِیْنَ.\nO He remembrance of Whom gives distinction to the rememberers, O He thankfulness unto Whom renders the thankful successful, O He praise of Whom gives honour to the praisers, O He obedi¬ence unto Whom delivers the obedient, O He Whose door is kept open for the beseechers, O He Whose path is evident to those who turn to (Him), O He Whose signs are arguments for those who look into, O He Whose Book (Holy Quran) is the conversation of the pious, O He Who gives liveli¬hood in general to the disobedient as good as to the obedient, O He Whose mercy is near at hand to the virtuous.\n(76) To Cure Leprosy\nYAA MAN TABAARAKASMOHU, YAA MAN TA-A’ALA JADDOHU, YAA MAN LAA ELAAHA GHAYROHU, YAA MAN JALLA SANAA-OHU, YAA MAN TAQADDASAT ASMAA-OHU, YAA MAYN-YADOOMO BAQAA-OHU, YAA MANIL A’ZAMATO BAHAA-OHU, YAA MANIL KIBREYAA-O REDAA-OHU YAA MAN LAA TOHSAA AALAA-OHU YAA MAN LAA TO-A’DDO NA’MAAOHU.\nیَا مَنْ تَبَارَکَ اسْمُہٗ یَا مَنْ تَعَالٰی جَدُّہٗ یَا مَنْ لَّا اِلٰہَ غَیْرُہٗ یَا مَنْ جَلَّ ثَنَآؤُہٗ یَا مَنْ تَقَدَّسَتْ اَسْمَآؤُہٗ یَا مَنْ یَّدُوْمُ بَقَآؤُہٗ یَا مَنِ الْعَظَمَۃُ بَہَآؤُہٗ یَا مَنِ الْکِبْرِیَآءُ رِدَآؤُہٗ یَا مَنْ لَا تُحْصٰی اٰلَآؤُہٗ یَا مَنْ لَا تُعَدُّ نَعْمَآؤُہٗ.\nO He Whose name brings blessings in abun¬dance, O He Whose nobility is praiseworthy, O He other than Who there is no god, O He Whose praise is glorious, O He Whose names are holy, O He Whose continuance is ever-lasting, O He Whose brilliance Is extensive, O He Whose pride is His companion, O He summing up of Whose bestow¬als is not possible, O He Whose innumerable bounties are countless.\n(77) To Liquidate Debts\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA YAA MO-E’ENO, YAA AMEENO, YAA MOBEENO, YA MATEENO, YAA MAKEENO YAA RASHEEDO, YAA HAMEEDO, YAA MAJEEDO, YAA SHADEEDO, YAA SHAHEEDO.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَا مُعِیْنُ یَآ اَمِیْنُ یَا مُبِیْنُ یَا مَتِیْنُ یَا مَکِیْنُ یَا رَشِیْدُ یَا حَمِیْدُ یَا مَجِیْدُ یَا شَدِیْدُ یَا شَہِیْدُ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O Who lends a hand, O Trustworthy, O Distinct, O Perse¬vering, O Permanently Established, O Who guides well, O Praiseworthy, O Celebrated, O Severe, O Witness.\n(78) To Receive Love And Affection\nYAA ZAL A’RSHIL MAJEEDE, YAA ZAL QAWLIS SADEEDE, YAA ZAL FE’LIR RASHEEDE, YAA ZAL BATSHISH SHADEED, YAA ZAL WA’DE WAL-WA-E’EDE, YAA MAN HOWAL WALIYYUL HAMEEDO, YAA MAN HOWA FA-A’ALUL LEMAA YOREEDO, YAA MAN HOWA QAREEBUN GHAYRA BA-E’EDIN, YAA MAN HOWA A’LAA KULLE SHAY-IN SHAHEEDUN, YAA MAN HOWA LAYSA BE-ZALLAAMIL LIL-A’BEEDE.\nیَا ذَا الْعَرْشِ الْمَجِیْدِ یَا ذَا الْقَوْلِ السَّدِیْدِ یَا ذَا الْفِعْلِ الرَّشِیْدِ یَا ذَا البَطْشِ الشَّدِیْدِ یَا ذَا الْوَعْدِ وَالْوَعِیْدِ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ الْوَلِیُّ الْحَمِیْدُ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فَعَّالٌ لِّمَا یُرِیْدُ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ قَرِیْبٌ غَیْرُ بَعِیْدٍ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ عَلٰی کُلِّ شَیْءٍ شَہِیْدٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ لَیْسَ بِظَلَّامٍ لِّلْعَبِیْدِ.\nO Lord of the glorious throne, O Lord of truthful words, O Lord of deeds and guidance, O Hard Taskmaster, O Lord of hope and fear, O He Who is a praiseworthy friend, O He Who does whatever He wills, O He Who is near, not far, O He Who is a witness over all things, O He Who does not oppress His servants.\n(79) To Seek Freedom From Impris¬onment\nYAA MAN LAA SHAREEKA LAHU WA LAA WAZEERA, YAA MAN LAA SHABEEHA LAHU WA LAA NAZEERA, YAA KHALEQASH SHAMSE WAL-QAMARIL MONEERE, YAA MUGHNEYAL BAA-E’SIL-FAQEERE YAA RAAZEKAT TIFLIS SAGHEERE, YAA RAAHEMASH SHAYKHIL KABEERE, YAA JAABERAL A’ZMIL KASEERE, YAA I’SMATAL KHAA-E’FIL MUSTAJEERE, YAA MAN HOWA BE-EBAADEHI KHABEERUN BASEEROON, YAA MAN HOWA A’LA KULLE SHAY-IN QADEERUN.\nیَا مَنْ لَّا شَرِیْکَ لَہٗ وَ لَا وَزِیْرَ یَا مَنْ لَّا شَبِیْہَ لَہٗ وَ لَا نَظِیْرَ یَا خَالِقَ الشَّمْسِ وَالْقَمَرِ الْمُنِیْرِ یَا مُغْنِیَ الْبَآئِسِ الْفَقِیْرِ یَا رَازِقَ الطِّفْلِ الصَّغِیْرِ یَا رَاحِمَ الشَّیْخِ الْکَبِیْرِ یَا جَابِرَ الْعَظْمِ الْکَسِیْرِ یَا عِصْمَۃَ الْخَآئِفِ الْمُسْتَجِیْرِ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ بِعِبَادِہٖ خَبِیْرٌ بَصِیْرٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ عَلٰی کُلِّ شَیْءٍ قَدِیْرٌ.\nO He Who shares not with a partner, nor takes up an assistant, O He unto Whom there is no likeness, nor analogy, O Creator of the sun and the bright moon, O Who makes the listless poor rich, O Who arranges food for the just born baby, O Who takes care of the old age, O Who sets broken bones, O Who keeps watch over the afraid peti-tioners, O He Who is All-Knowing and All-Seeing towards His servants, O He Who wields absolute power over all things.\n(80) To Seek Prosperity\nYAA ZAL JOODE WAN-NE-A’ME, YAA ZAL FAZLE WAL-KARAME, YAA KHAALEQAL LAWHE WAL-QALAME, YAA BAARE-AZ ZARRE WAN-NASAME, YAA ZAL BAASE WAN-NEQAME, YAA MULHEMAL A’RABE WAL A’JAME, YAA KASHEFAZ ZURRE WAL-ALAME, YAA A’ALEMAS SIRRE WAL-HEMAME, YAA RABBAL BAYTE WAL-HARAME, YAA MAN KHALAQAL ASHYAA-A MENAL A’DAME.\nیَا ذَا الْجُوْدِ وَالنِّعَمِ یَا ذَا الْفَضْلِ وَالْکَرَمِ یَا خَالِقَ اللَّوْحِ وَالْقَلَمِ یَا بَارِءَ الذَّرِّ وَالنَّسَمِ یَا ذَا الْبَاْسِ وَالنِّقَمِ یَا مُلْہِمَ الْعَرَبِ وَالْعَجَمِ یَا کَاشِفَ الضُّرِّ وَالْاَلَمِ یَا عَالِمَ السِّرِّ وَالْہِمَمِ یَا رَبَّ الْبَیْتِ وَالْحَرَمِ یَا مَنْ خَلَقَ الْاَشْیَآءَ مِنَ الْعَدَمِ.\nO Lord of plenty and comforts, O Lord of super abundance and generosity, O Creator of Lawh (smooth surfaced material to write) and Qalam (pen), O Who created ants and human beings, O Lord of power and punishment, O who inspires Arabs and non-Arabs, O Disperser of Hardships and sorrows, O Knower of secrets and intentions, O Lord of the House and the sacred precinct (Holy Kaabah and its surroundings), O He Who brought forth things from the unknown.\n(81) To Cure Migraine\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA, BISMEKA, YAA FAA-E’LO, YAA JAA-E’LO, YAA QAABELO, YAA KAAMELO, YAA FAASELO, YAA FAAZELO YAA A’ADELO, YAA GHALEBO, YAA TAALEBO, YAA WAAHEBO.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَا فَاعِلُ یَا جَاعِلُ یَا قَابِلُ یَا کَامِلُ یَا فَاصِلُ یَا وَاصِلُ یَا عَادِلُ یَا غَالِبُ یَا طَالِبُ یَا وَاہِبُ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O Executor, O Maker, O Receiver, O Complete, O Cultivated, O Uniter, O Just, O Who overcomes, O Who demands, O Who gives gifts.\n(82) To Cure Ulcer\nYAA MAN AN-A’MA BE-TAWLEHI, YAA MAN AKRAMA BE-JOODEHI, YAA MAN JAADA BE-LUTFEHI, YAA MAN TA-A’ZZAZA BE-QUDRATEHI, YAA MAN QADDARA BE-HIMMATEHI, YAA MAN HAKAMA BE-TADBEEREHI, YAA MAN DABBARA BE-I’LMEHI, YAA MAN TAJAWAZA BE-HILMEHI, YAA MAN DANA FEE O’LUWWEHI, YAA MAN A’LAA FEE ZONUWWEHI.\nیَا مَنْ اَنْعَمَ بِطَوْلِہٖ یَا مَنْ اَکْرَمَ بِجُوْدِہٖ یَا مَنْ جَادَ بِلُطْفِہٖ یَا مَنْ تَعَزَّزَ بِقُدْرَتِہٖ یَا مَنْ قَدَّرَ بِحِکْمَتِہٖ یَا مَنْ حَکَمَ بِتَدْبِیْرِہٖ یَا مَنْ دَبَّرَ بِعِلْمِہٖ یَا مَنْ تَجَاوَزَ بِحِلْمِہٖ یَا مَنْ دَنٰی فِیْ عُلُوِّہٖ یَا مَنْ عَلاَ فِیْ دُنُوِّہٖ.\nO He Who gives long lasting rewards, O He Who is abundantly generous, O He Who is effec¬tually kind, O He Who confers honour with author¬ity, O He Who ordains with wisdom, O He Who arbitrates with discretion, O He Who directs through knowledge, O He Who is indulgent out of forbear¬ance, O He Who is near in spite of highness, O He Who is High notwithstanding the nearness.\n(83) To Cure Backache\nYAA MAYN YAKHLOQO MAA YASHAA-O’, YAA MAYN YAF-A’LO MAA YASHAA-O’, YAA MAYN YAHDI MAN YASHAA-O’, YAA MAYN YOZILLO MAYN YASHAA-O’, YAA MAYN YO-A’ZZEBO MAYN YASHAA-O’, YAA MAYN YAGHFERO LEMAYN-YASHAA-O’, YAA MAYN YO-I’ZZO MAYN YASHAA-O’, YAA MAYN YOZILLO MAYN YASHAA-O YAA MAYN YOSAWWERO FIL-ARHAAME MAA YASHAA-O’, YAA MAYN YAKHTASSO BE-RAHMATEHI MAYN-YASHAA-O’.\nیَا مَنْ یَّخْلُقُ مَا یَشَآءُ یَا مَنْ یَفْعَلُ مَا یَشَآءُ یَا مَنْ یَہْدِیْ مَنْ یَّشَآءُ یَا مَنْ یُّضِلُّ مَنْ یَّشَآءُ یَا مَنْ یُّعَذِّبُ مَنْ یَّشَآءُ یَا مَنْ یَغْفِرُ لِمَنْ یَّشَآءُ یَا مَنْ یُعِزُّ مَنْ یَّشَآءُ یَا مَنْ یُضِلُّ مَنْ یَّشَآءُ یَا مَنْ یُّصَوِّرُ فِی الْاَرْحَامِ مَا یَشَآءُ یَا مَنْ یَّخْتَصُّ بِرَحْمَتِہٖ مَنْ یَّشَآءُ.\nO He Who creates whatever He wants, O He Who does Whatever He wills, O He Who guides whomsoever He chooses, O He Who abandons whomsoever he desieres, O He Who punishes Whomsoever He condemns, O He Who forgives whomsoever He prefers, O He Who elevates whom-soever He takes up, O He Who humiliates whom¬soever He dislikes, O He Who gives shape (to bodies) in the wombs howsoever He likes, O He Who elects, with His mercy, whomsoever He favours.\n(84) To Cure Pain In The Right Ribs\nYAA MAN LAM YATTAKHIZ SAAHEBATAN WA LAA WALADAN, YAA MAN JA-A’LA LE KULLE SHAY-IN QADRA, YAA MAN-LAA YUSHREKO FEE HUKMEHI AHADAN, YAA MAN JA-A’LAL MALAA-EKATO ROSOLAN, YAA MAN JA-A’LA FIS-SAMAA-E BOROOJAN YAA MAN JA-A’LAL ARZA QARAARAN, YAA MAN KHALAQA MENAL MAAA-E BASHARAN, YAA MAN JA-A’LA LE-KULLE SHAY-IN AMADAN, YAA MAN AHAATA BE-KULLE SHAY-IN I’LMAN, YAA MAN AHSA KULLA SHAY-IN A’DADAN.\nیَا مَنْ لَّمْ یَتَّخِذْ صَاحِبَۃً وَّلاَ وَلَدًا یَا مَنْ جَعَلَ لِکُلِّ شَیْءٍ قَدْرًا یَا مَنْ لَّا یُشْرِکُ فِی حُکْمِہٖ اَحَدًا یَا مَنْ جَعَلَ الْمَلَآئِکَۃِ رُسُلًا یَا مَنْ جَعَلَ فِی السَّمَآءِ بُرُوْجًا یَا مَنْ جَعَلَ الْاَرْضَ قَرَارًا یَا مَنْ خَلَقَ مِنَ الْمَآءِ بَشَرًا یَا مَنْ جَعَلَ لِکُلِّ شَیْءٍ اَمَدًا یَا مَنْ اَحَاطَ بِکُلِّ شَیْءٍ عِلْمًا یَا مَنْ اَحْصٰی کُلَّ شَیْءٍ عَدَدًا.\nO He Who did not take to wife, nor beget children, O He Who took stock of the utility of all things, O He Who does not share with anyone to issue His orders, O He Who selected Angels as messengers, O He Who appointed stations in the heavens, O He Who rendered the earth stable and steady, O He Who creates man from the sperm, O He Who determines limits for all things, O He Who is aware of everything thorough knowledge, O He Who enumerates the calculation (terms) of everything.\n(85) To Cure Pain In The Waist\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA YAA AWWALO, YAA AAKHERO, YAA ZAAHERO, YAA BAATENO, YAA BARRO, YAA HAQQO, YAA FARDO, YAA WITRO, YAA SAMADO, YAA SARMADO.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَآ اَوَّلُ یَآ اٰخِرُ یَا ظَاہِرُ یَا بَاطِنُ یَا بَرُّ یَا حَقُّ یَا فَرْدُ یَا وِتْرُ یَا صَمَدُ یَا سَرْمَدُ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O First, O Last, O Hidden, O Evident, O Pious, O Real, O Single, O One and Only, O Independent, O Ever-Lasting.\n(86) To Cure Spleen Ailments\nYAA KHAYRA MA’ROOFIN O’OREFA YAA AFZALA MA’BOODIN O’BEDA, YAA AJALLA MASHKOORIN SHOKERA, YAA A-A’ZZA MAZKOORIN ZOKERA, YAA A-A’LAA MAHMOODIN HOMEDA, YAA AQDAMA MAWJOODIN TOLEBA, YAA ARFA-A’ MAWSOOFIN WOSEFA, YAA AKBARA MAQSOODIN QOSEDA, YAA AKRAMA MAS-O’OLIN SO-ELA, YAA ASHRAFA MAHBOOBIN O’LEMA.\nیَا خَیْرَ مَعْرُوْفٍ عُرِفَ یَآ اَفْضَلَ مَعْبُوْدٍ عُبِدَ یَآ اَجَلَّ مَشْکُوْرٍ شُکِرَ یَآ اَعَزَّ مَذْکُوْرٍ ذُکِرَ یَآ اَعْلٰی مَحْمُوْدٍ حُمِدَ یَآ اَقْدَمَ مَوْجَوْدٍ طُلِبَ یَآ اَرْفَعَ مَوْصُوْفٍ وُصِفَ یَآ اَکْبَرَ مَقْصُوْدٍ قُصِدَ یَآ اَکْرَمَ مَسْئُوْلٍ سُئِلَ یَآ اَشْرَفَ مَحْبُوْبٍ عُلِمَ.\nO Well-Known, thoroughly acknowledged, O Most Excellent Worship able, devotedly worshiped, O Most Illustrious Thank-Worthy, gratefully thanked, O Dearest Memorable, sincerely remem¬bered, O Highest Praiseworthy, thankfully praised, O Foremost Supreme Being, longingly beseeched, O Most Elated Attributable, distinguishedly de¬scribed, O The Greatest purpose, eagerly strived for, O Most Generous entreatingly requested, O Noblest Beloved, ardently recognised.\n(87) To Cure Headache\nYAA HABEEBAL BAAKEENA YAA SAYYEDAL MOTAWAKKELEENA, YAA HAADEYAL MOZILLEENA, YAA WALIYYAL MO-AMENEENA, YAA ANEESAZ ZAAKEREENA, YAA MAFZA-A’L MALHOOFEENA, YAA MUNJEYAS SAADEQEENA, YAA AQDARAL QAADREENA, YAA A-A’LAMAL A’ALEMEENA YAA ELAAHAL KHALQE AJMAE’ENA.\nیَا حَبِیْبَ الْبَاکِیْنَ یَا سَیِّدَ الْمُتَوَکِّلِیْنَ یَا ہَادِیَ الْمُضِلِّیْنَ یَا وَلِیَّ الْمُؤْمِنِیْنَ یَآ اَنِیْسَ الذَّاکِرِیْنَ یَا مَفْزَعَ الْمَلْہُوْفِیْنَ یَا مُنْجِیَ الصَّادِقِیْنَ یَآ اَقْدَرَ الْقَادِرِیْنَ یَآ اَعْلَمَ الْعَالِمِیْنَ یَآ اِلٰہَ الْخَلْقِ اَجْمَعِیْنَ.\nO Friend of the grief stricken, O Firm Support¬er of those who rely upon (Him), O Guide of the wayward, O Guardian of the faithful, O Compan¬ion of the rememberers, O Refuge of the unhappy, O Redeemer of the truthful, O the Most Powerful of powerfuls, O The Best of knowers, O God of all creation.\n(88) To Cure Pain In Forehead\nYAA MAN A’LAA FAQAHARA, YAA MAN MALAKA FAQADARA, YAA MAN BATANA FAKHABARA, YAA MAN O’BEDA FASHAKARA YAA MAN O’SEYA FAGHAFARA YAA MAN LAA TAHWEEHIL FEKARO, YAA MAN LA YOODREKOHU BASARUN YAA MAN LAA YAKHFAA A’LAYHE ASARUN YAA RAAZEQAL BASHARE, YAA MOQADDERA KULLE QADARIN.\nیَا مَنْ عَلاَ فَقَہَرَ یَا مَنْ مَّلَکَ فَقَدَرَ یَا مَنْ بَطَنَ فَخَبَرَ یَا مَنْ عُبِدَ فَشَکَرَ یَا مَنْ عُصِیَ فَغَفَرَ یَا مَنْ لَّا تَحْوِیْہِ الْفِکَرُ یَا مَنْ لَّا یُدْرِکُہٗ بَصَرٌ یَا مَنْ لَّا یَخْفٰی عَلَیْہِ اَثَرٌ یَا رَازِقَ الْبَشَرِ یَا مُقَدِّرَ کُلِّ قَدَرٍ.\nO He Who is High so overpowers, O He Who is Master so preordains, O He Who penetrates hearts so is aware, O He Who is worshiped and acknowledges, O He Who is disobeyed yet for¬gives, O He Whom intellect cannot grasp, O He Whom insight cannot conceive, O He from Whose investigation nothing can be kept secret, O Provid¬er of livelihood, O Ordainer of every destiny.\n(89) To Cure Non-Stop Urination\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA YAA HAAFEZO, YAA BAAREO, YAA ZAAREO YAA BAAZEKHO, YAA FAAREJO, YAA FAATEHO, YAA KAASHEFO, YAA ZAAMENO YAA AAMERO, YAA NAHEYO.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَا حَافِظُ یَا بَارِءُ یَا ذَارِءُ یَا بَاذِخُ یَا فَارِجُ یَا فَاتِحُ یَا کَاشِفُ یَا ضَامِنُ یَآ اٰمِرُ یَا نَاہِیْ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O Guardian, O Creator, O Multiplier, O Very Proud, O Reliever, O Conqueror, O Investigator, O Guar¬antor, O Governor, O Prohibiter.\n(90) To Cure Pain In Navel\nYAA MAN LAA YA’LAMUL GHAYBA ILLAA HOWA, YAA MAN LAA YASREFUS SOO-A ILLAA HOWA, YAA MAN LAA YAKHLOQUL KHALQA ILLAA HOWA, YAA MAN LAA YAGHFERUZ ZONOOBA ILLAA HOWA, YAA MAN LAA YOTIMMUN NEA’-MATA ILLAA HOWA, YAA MAN LAA YOQALLEBUL QOLOOBA ILLAA HOWA, YAA MAN LAA YODABBERUL AMRA ILLAA HOWA, YAA MAN LAA YONAZZELUL GHAYSA ILLAA HOWA, YAA MAN LAA YABSOTUR RIZQA ILLAA HOWA, YAA MAN LAA YOHYIL-MAWTA ILLAA HOWA.\nیَا مَنْ لَّا یَعْلَمُ الْغَیْبَ اِلَّا ہُوَ یَا مَنْ لَا یَصْرِفُ السُّوْٓءَ اِلَّا ہُوَ یَا مَنْ لَّا یَخْلُقُ الْخَلْقَ اِلَّا ہُوَ یَا مَنْ لَّا یَغْفِرُ الذُّنُوْبَ اِلَّا ہُوَ یَا مَنْ لَّا یُتِمُّ النِّعْمَۃَ اِلَّا ہُوَ یَا مَنْ لَّا یُقَلِّبُ الْقُلُوْبَ اِلَّا ہُوَ یَا مَنْ لَّا یُدَبِّرُ الْاَمْرَ اِلَّا ہُوَ یَا مَنْ لَّا یُنَزِّلُ الْغَیْثَ اِلَّا ہُوَ یَا مَنْ لَّا یَبْسُطُ الرِّزْقَ اِلَّا ہُوَ یَا مَنْ لَّا یُحْیِ الْمَوْتٰی اِلَّا ہُوَ.\nO He Who alone, and no one else, knows the unknown, O He Who alone, and no one else, drives away evil, O He Who alone, and no one else, creates the creation, O He Who alone, and no one else, forgives the sins, O He Who alone, and no one else, effects the bounties, O He Who alone, and no one else, makes hearts turn to (Him), O He Who alone, and no one else, directs administration, O He Who alone, and no one else, sends down abundant and far-spread rain, O He Who alone, and on one else, liberally distributes sustenance, O He Who alone, and no one else, brings back the dead to life.\n(91) To Remove The Stone From Bladder\nYAA MO-E’ENAZ ZOAFAA-E, YAA SAAHEBAL GHORA-BAA-E, YAA NAASERAL AWLEYAA-E, YAA QAAHERAL A-A’DAA-E, YAA RAAFEAS SAMAA-E YAA ANEESAL ASFEYAA-E, YAA HABEEBAL ATQEYAA-E, YAA KANZAL FOQARAA-E, YAA ELAAHAL AGHNEYAA-E, YAA AKRAMAL KORAMAA-E.\nیَا مُعِیْنَ الضُّعَفَآءِ یَا صَاحِبَ الْغُرَبَآءِ یَا نَاصِرَ الْاَوْلِیَآءِ یَا قَاہِرَ الْاَعْدَآءِ یَا رَافِعَ السَّمَآءِ یَآ اَنِیْسَ الْاَصْفِیَآءِ یَا حَبِیْبَ الْاَتْقِیَآءِ یَا کَنْزَ الْفُقَرَآءِ یَآ اِلٰہَ الْاَغْنِیَآءِ یَا اَکْرَمَ الْکُرَمَآءِ.\nO Supporter of the weak, O Companion of the forsaken, O Helper of friends, O Subduer of ene¬mies, O Raiser of the sky, O Comrade of the sincerely attached, O Friend of the pious, O En-richer of the have nots, O God of the rich, O Honourer of the generous.\n(92) To Cure Piles\nYAA KAAFEYA MIN KULLE SHAY-IN YAA QAA-E’MO A’LAA KULLE SHAY-IN, YAA MAN LAA YUSHBEHOHU SHAY-UN, YAA MAN LAA YAZEEDO