MEETAHU, YAA KHAALEQA KULLE SHAY-IN WA WAARESAHU.\nیَآ اَوَّلَ کُلِّ شَیْءٍ وَّ اٰخِرَہٗ یَا اِلٰہَ کُلِّ شَیْءٍ وَّمَلِیْکَہٗ یَا رَبَّ کُلِّ شَیْءٍ وَّ صَانِعَہٗ یَا بَارِءَ کُلِّ شَیْءٍ وَّ خَالِقَہٗ یَا قَابِضَ کُلِّ شَیْءٍ وَّ بَاسِطَہٗ یَا مُبْدِءَ کُلِّ شَیْءٍ وَّ مُعِیْدَہٗ یَا مُنْشِئَ کُلِّ شَیْءٍ وَّ مُقَدِّرَہٗ یَا مُکَوِّنَ کُلِّ شَیْءٍ وَّ مُحَوِّلَہٗ یَا مُحْیِیَ کُلِّ شَیْءٍ وَّ مُمِیْتَہٗ یَا خَالِقَ کُلِّ شَیْءٍ وَّ وَارِثَہٗ.\nO Beginning and End of all things, O God and King of all things, O Lord and maker of all things, O Originator and Creator of all things, O Seizer and Spreader of all things, O Inventor and Resurrecter of all things, O Author and Pre-ordainer of all things, O Establisher and Abolisher of all things, O Who brings everything to life and puts everything to death, O Producer and Possessioner of all things.\n(95) To Cure Stomachache\nYAA KHAYRA ZAAKERIN WA MAZKOORIN, YAA KHAYRA SHAKERIN WA MASHKOORIN, YAA KHAYRA HAAMEDIN WA MAHMOODIN, YAA KHAYRA SHAAHEDIN WA MASH-HOODIN, YAA KHAYRA DAA-I’N WA MAD-O’OWWIN, YAA KHAYRA MOJEEBIN WA MOOJAABIN, YAA KHAYRA MOONESIN WA ANEESIN YAA KHAYRA SAAHEBIN WA JALEESIN, YAA KHAYRA MAQSOODIN WA MATLOOBIN, YAA KHAYRA HABEEBIN WA MAHBOOBIN.\nیَا خَیْرَ ذَاکِرٍ وَّ مَذْکُوْرٍ یَّا خَیْرَ شَاکِرِوَّ مَشْکُوْرٍ یَا خَیْرَ حَامِدٍ وَّ مَحْمُوْدٍ یَا خَیْرَ شَاہِدٍ وَّ مَشْہُوْدٍ یَا خَیْرَ دَاعٍ وَّ مَدْعُوٍّ یَا خَیْرَ مُجِیْبٍ وَّ مُجَابٍ یَا خَیْرَ مُوْنِسٍ وَّ اَنِیْسٍ یَا خَیْرَ صَاحِبٍ وَّ جَلِیْسٍ یَا خَیْرَ مَقْصُوْدٍ وَّ مَطْلُوْبٍ یَا خَیْرَ حَبِیْبٍ وَّ مَحْبُوْبٍ.\nO Who remembers excellently and likewise is remembered, O Who expresses appreciation ex¬cellently and likewise is appreciated, O Who Priases excellently and likewise is praised, O Who bears testimony excellently and likewise is testified, O Who calls up excellently and likewise is called upon, O Who gives response excellently and like¬wise is responded, O Excellent sympathizer and consoler, O Excellent Companion and comrade, O Excellent Goal and Aim, O Excellent Intimate and Beloved.\n(96) To Cure Knee Pain\nYAA MAN HOWA LEMAN DA-AA’HO MOJEEBUN, YAA MAN HOWA LEMAN ATAA-A’HU HABEEBUN, YAA MAN HOWA ELAA MAN AHABBAHU QAREEBUN, YAA MAN HOWA BEMANIS TAHFAZAHU RAQEEBUN, YAA MAN HOWA BEMAN RAJAAHO KAREEMUN, YAA MAN HOWA BEMAN A’SAAHO HALEEMUN YAA MAN HOWA FEE A’ZAMATEHI RAHEEMOON, YAA MAN HOWA FEE HIKMATEHI A’ZEEMUN, YAA MAN HOWA FEE EHSAANEHI QADEEMUN, YAA MAN HOWA BEMAN ARAADAHU A’LEEMUN.\nیَا مَنْ ہُوَ لِمَنْ دَعَاہُ مُجِیْبُ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ لِمَنْ اَطَاعُہٗ حَبِیْبٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ اِلٰی مَنْ اَحَبَّہٗ قَرِیْبٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ بِمَنِ اسْتَحْفَظَہٗ رَقِیْبٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ بِمَنْ رَجَاہُ کَرِیْمٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ بِمَنْ عَصَاہٗ حَلِیْمٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ عَظَمَتِہٖ رَحِیْمٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ حِکْمَتِہٖ عَظِیْمٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ فِیْ اِحْسَانِہٖ قَدِیْمٌ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ بِمَنْ اَرَادَہٗ عَلِیْمٌ.\nO He Who answers to him who calls out, O He Who is ally of him who obeys, O He Who is near to him who loves (Him), O He Who is sentinel of him who asks for (His) protection, O He Who is Generous to him who makes a request (to Him), O He Who is indulgent towards him who disobeys, O He Who, in His greatness, is Merciful, O He Who, in His wisdom is great, O He Who, in His benev¬olence, is foremost, O He Who is aware of him who desires (Him).\n(97) To Cure Throat Pain\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKA YAA MOSABBEBO, YAA MORAGHGHEBO, YAA MOQALLEBO, YAA MO-A’QQEBO, YAA MORATTEBO, YAA MOKHAWWEFO, YAA MOHAZZERO, YAA MOZAKKERO, YAA MOSAKHKHERO, YAA MOGHAYYERO.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ یَا مُسَبِّبُ یَا مُرَغِّبُ یَا مُقَلِّبُ یَا مُعَقِّبُ یَا مُرَتِّبُ یَا مُخَوِّفُ یَا مُحَذِّرُ یَا مُذَکِّرُ یَا مُسَخِّرُ یَا مُغَیِّرُ.\nO Allah I beseech Thee in Thy name, O Prime Cause, O Who inspires desires, O Who makes adjustments, O Who punishes, O Who arranges, O Who alarms, O Who warns, O Who reminds, O Who subdues, O Who transforms.\n(98) To Seek Fulfilment of Legiti¬mate Desire\nYAA MAN I’LMOHU SAABEQUN, YAA MAN WA’DOHU SAADEQUN, YAA MAN LUTFOHU ZAAHERUN, YAA MAN AMROHU GHALEBUN, YAA MAN KETAABOHU MOHKAMUN, YAA MAN QAZAA-A’HU KAA-ENUN, YAA MAN QURAANOHU MAJEEDUN, YAA MAN MULKOHU QADEEMUN, YAA MAN FAZLOHU A’MEEMUN, YAA MAN ARSHOHU A’ZEEMUN.\nیَا مَنْ عِلْمُہٗ سَابِقٌ یَا مَنْ وَعْدُھٗ صَادِقٌ یَا مَنْ لُطْفُہٗ ظَاہِرٌ یَا مَنْ اَمْرُہٗ غَالِبٌ یَا مَنْ کِتَابُہٗ مُحْکَمٌ یَا مَنْ قَضَآءُہٗ کَآئِنٌ یَا مَنْ قُرْاٰنُہٗ مُجِیْدٌ یَا مَنْ مُلْکُہٗ قَدِیْمٌ یَا مَنْ فَضْلُہٗ عَمِیْمٌ یَا مَنْ عَرْشُہٗ عَظِیْمٌ.\nO He Whose knowledge is a priori, O He Whose promise is true, O He Whose kindness is evident, O He Whose command is prevalent, O He Whose Book is certain, O He Whose decision is carried through, O He Whose Quran is glorious, O He Whose kingdom is eternal, O He Whose favour is all-embracing, O He Whose throne is sublime.\n(99) To Cure Pain In Legs\nYAA MAN LAA YASH-GHOLOHU SAM-U’N A’N SAM-I’N, YAA MAN LAA YAMNA-O’HU FEA’LUN A’N FEA’LIN, YAA MAN LAA YULHEEHE QAWLUN A’N QAWLIN, YAA MAN LAA YOGHALLETOHU SO-A’LUN A’N SO-A’LIN, YAA MAN LAA YAHJOBOHU SHAY-IN A’N SHAY-IN YAA MAN LAA YUBREMOHU ILHAAHUL MOLEHHEENA YAA MAN HOWA GHAAYATO MORAADIL MOREEDEENA, YAA MAN HOWA MUNTAHAA HEMAMIL A’AREFEENA, YAA MAN HOWA MUN-TAHAA TALABIT TAALEBEENA, YAA MAN LAA YAKHFA A’LAYHE ZARRATUN FIL A’ALAMEENA.\nیَا مَنْ لَّا یَشْغَلُہٗ سَمْعٌ عَنْ سَمْعٍ یَا مَنْ لَّا یَمْنَعُہٗ فِعْلٌ عَنْ فِعلٍ یَا مَنْ لَّا یُلْہِیْہِ قَوْلٌ عَنْ قَوْلٍ یَا مَنْ لَّا یُغَلِّطُہٗ سُؤَالٌ عَنْ سُؤَالٍ یَا مَنْ لَّا یَحْجُبُہٗ شَیْءٌ عَنْ شَیْءٍ یَا مَنْ لَّا یُبْرِمُہٗ اِلحَاحُ الْمُلِحِّیْنَ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ غَایَۃُ مُرَادِ الْمُرِیْدِیْنَ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ مُنْتَہٰی ہِمَمِ الْعَارِفِیْنَ یَا مَنْ ہُوَ مُنْتَہٰی طَلَبِ الطَّالِبِیْنَ یَا مَنْ لَا یَخْفٰی عَلَیْہِ ذَرَّۃٌ فِی الْعَالَمِیْنَ.\nO He Whom one audience does not keep away from hearing another, O He Whom one action does not prevent from executing another, O He Whom one address does not prevent from delivering another, O He Whom one question does not draw apart from another, O He for Whom one object does not get in the way of another, O He Whom importunity of intimidators does not make ill-tempered, O He Who is the Last resort of the wishes of the devotees, O He Who is the ultimate goal of the aspirations of the intelligent, O He Who is the ultimate means of fulfilment of the beseechers, O He from Whom not even the minutest unit matter is hidden.\n(100) To Cure Thigh Pain\nYAA HALEEMAN LAA YA’JALO, YAA JAWAADAN LAA YABKHALO, YAA SAADEQAN LAA YUKHLEFO, YAA WAHHAABAN LAA YAMALLO, YAA QAAHERAN LAA YUGHLABO, YAA A’ZEEMAN LAA YOOSAFO, YAA A’DLAN LAA YAHEEFO, YAA GHANIYYAN LAA YAFTAQERO YAA KABEERAN LAA YASGHORO YAA HAAFEZAN LAA YAGHFOLO.\nیَا حَلِیْمًا لَا یَعْجَلُ یَا جَوَادًا لَا یَبْخَلُ یَا صَادِقًا لَا یُخْلِفُ یَا وَہَّابًا لَا یَمَلُّ یَاقَاہِرًا لَا یُغْلَبُ یَا عَظِیْمًا لَا یُوْصَفُ یَا عَدْلاً لَا یَحِیْفُ یَا غَنِیًّا لَا یَفْتَقِرُ یَا کَبِیْرًا لَا یَصْغُرُ یَا حَافِظًا لَّا یَغْفُلُ.\nO Forbearing Who does not make haste, O Liberal Bestower Who never supplies sparingly, O Truthful Who never turns away, O Awarder Who never regrets, O Dominant Who is never overpow¬ered, O Sublime Who cannot be described, O Just Who does not oppress, O Rich Who cannot be rendered poor, O Great Who cannot be rendered small, O Guardian Who does not neglect.", 
    "title": "Dua Jawshan al Kabir"
}